product_title: WOW Toys Town Advent Calendar
review_headline: We love how well they are made
review_body: We have MANY Wow toys in our home.  We love how well they are made.  The advent calendar is an exception.  The plastic is thinner than our other wow toys and the barn animals won't even stand up on their own due to the head weighing more than the body and uneven base of the toy.  Very disappointing when we love the concept.  The story to read along with everyday is great.  I would have preferred quality (and would have paid more for it) instead of a cheap "knock-off" of the rest of their toy line.  It is very obvious by the weight of the toys sloppy paint jobs which items in our "Wow Toys" bin are part advent calendar vs. the rest of the toys we have.  Also there is a lot of overlap between the wow town advent calendar & winter wonderland calendar, which makes me want to look for alternatives for this year's advent calendar options.

product_title: Paraboard - Parallel Charging Board for Lipos with EC5 Connectors
review_headline: CAN SAVE TME IF YOU UNDESTAND HOW IT WORKS .
review_body: Works well ,quality product but this style of board will charge multiple batteries at the same time SAFELY  ( IF )  ALL BATTERIES ARE OF THE SAME CELL COUNT , THE SAME BATTERY COMPOSITION ( LIPO, NIMH-etc ) AND THEY MUST HAVE INDIVIDUAL CELL VOLTAGES THAT ARE VERY CLOSE AND EQUAL TO EACH BATTERY CONNECTED AT THE SAME TIME . When board is connected to most if not all chargers it can only read total and individual cell voltage of ONE OF THE BATTERIES AND MAY OVER OR UNDER CHARGE THE OTHERS TO SOME DEGREE , TOTAL RATE OF CHARGE IS DIVIDED EQUALLY BETWEEN BATTERIES CONNECTED AT THE SAME TIME . Close monitoring is a must  when using like all high discharge batteies . I  have only personally expeienced one lipo battery meltdown and it is a very  SHORT IF NOT  NON EXISTANT WINDOW OF OPPERUNITY TO PREVENT OR MINIMISE THE COLATTERAL DAMAGE ONCE THE PROCESS STARTS . Read and understand all charging and battery instructions .

product_title: ISLANDIA Wooden Resource Tokens Set for Both 3-4 and 5-6 Player Games (Compatible with Settlers) by Artificially Natural
review_headline: Catan is my husbands favorite game. We play all the time
review_body: Catan is my husbands favorite game.  We play all the time.  Due to many of our resource cards being damaged or missing, I hopped onto Amazon to look for a replacement deck.  While searching, I came across these tokens.  Who knew?!?!  (I was not aware a product like this existed.)  On a whim, I bought a pack.... and I'm soooo glad I did!  Everyone loved playing with the lil' tokens.  Call me crazy... but I think the game is just more fun when you are using a miniature sheep for a sheep, a miniature wood for a wood, etc... instead of plain ole cards.  It was easy.  We each kept our pieces in a small non-see-through cup during play (you can also play with your resources visible to all).  Not to mention... they were just a fraction of the price of the replacement deck I was going to buy online!  We are very happy with our purchase.  :)

product_title: Jake and The Never Land Pirates Shipwreck Beach Treasure Hunt Game, Yellow
review_headline: Cute and great deal for the price!
review_body: For the price, then game is awesome for a 3 year-old! Mine LOVES it. Be prepared to want to shoot yourself in the head after playing it for the umpteenth time in a row, but fun enough to entertain a preschooler (though would get boring pretty fast for an older child). Gameplay is simple enough to allow for young kiddos to play independently of an adult (if that is an option for you!) For like the $5-6 I paid for it, the game is interchangeable for just cheap but pretty sturdy pirate toys (even recycle the sword into a safe, lightweight Halloween costume accessory), so worth the price on that note alone. On the one hand, I love that the map (which you can't really see in the picture) is also a bag to hold the game, but would've preferred that the game packaging was reusable as a box as the map gets "deformed" by stuffing all the pieces in it and becomes somewhat of a pain to use as the flat playing surface necessary for the game (especially if you are not interested in pulling the little plastic stands off the treasure pieces every time which I imagine would also decrease the life of the pieces). This is of course easily solved by say putting it all in a gallon or bigger sized ziplock, or another box you have around, especially if you'd like it to stack nicely with your other games, but since I had to chuck all the packaging, would have been less wasteful if it was reusable. Overall, a fun and inexpensive game for the younger set which can be made super simple or a bit more challenging depending on how serious you are about hiding the treasure, and fun game/pirate-play pieces (just don't lose them!).

review_body: We received this free in our #bzzkit. My 8 year old son likes this toy a lot. First of all it was easy to get out of the package. Anymore that's the first plus. Second it had easy instructions to charge it and it didn't take long from box to playing. That was nice also.  It doesn't come with batteries so you'll need 4 AA batteries if you don't have them. The toy worked exactly as it said,  the helicopter launched from the truck and flew. The helicopter is the main toy here, the truck is just a bonus really. It's cool though. I'd say it's very durable also, he's played with it every day for about a week and a half or two weeks maybe and he's crashed it into everything. It's still holding up just fine. Overall I'd say it's a great two for one toy for the money if you buy it.

product_title: Madame Alexander Sweater Dressing 18" Doll
review_headline: Super Cute! Equal quality for much better price than American Girl Dolls
review_body:
Really cute doll, nice quality, cute clothes, 11 y.o. daughter loves it :o)

In my opinion the American Girls Dolls are seriously over priced and absolutely do not offer any superior quality oer the Madame Alexander dolls. It reminds me of the cabbage patch kids craze when folks would pay hundreds for those, only difference is that they had no competition of any sort, whereas the American Girl Dolls have tons of competition with other dolls of same size, idea, and quality. The Madame Alexander Dolls are a prime example.

This doll is really cute and my daughter really likes her. She says that the doll is cute, her outfit is cute and she especially loves the boots, She has 2-3 other Madame Alexander dolls plus 2 of the Springfield Collection dolls (sold at Michaels craft stores - cute but there are differences that make them obviously less expensively made than the Madame Alexander & American Girls.) She loves all her dolls and in fact has stated several times that she thinks the Madame Alexander dolls are "cuter and have more personality" than the American Girl Dolls.

Summary: Cute, good quality doll, good buy

product_title: Disney/Pixar - Super Chase - Cars Oversized Circus Cab - Radiator Springs - Diecast Vehicle
review_headline: One of the new Super Chase models for 2015!
review_body:
Circus Cab is the first "deluxe" model in the Super Chase line... Super Chase is a line of "Cars" and "Cars 2" 1:55 scale models Mattel began coming out with in 2011, which are SUPER rare (production limited to no more than 4000 world-wide), with Mattel's "deluxe" models (usually) meaning they're bigger in size than the regular models.

The 2015 Super Chase models (Circus Cab, Circus Van, Circus Sedan, Circus Pickup, and Circus Forklift & Circus GT) all stem from a scene that ran during the credits of the original "Cars" movie, in which Radiator Springs residents are watching car-related spoofs of popular Disney/Pixar films at the Radiator Springs Drive-In Theatre (Toy Car Story based on "Toy Story", Monster Trucks Inc. based on "Monster's Inc.", and this one based on 1998's "A Bug's Life".) In the short clip, it briefly shows the aforementioned circus cars, along with "A Bug's Life" character P.T. Flea now designed as a "Nimbly Co. No-See-Um LX", and "A Bug's Life" protagonist Flik designed as a "Special Aphid GT". (Both of those characters were released as part of a Mattel "Movie Moments" 2 pack years ago, with the non-speaking clown cars now being released as Super Chase.) Super Cab reminds us a bit of a green version of "Mack" from Disney's "Cars" movies, with Mack (voiced by John Ratzenberger) having some hilarious lines - he ALSO voices the Hamm car in Toy Car Story, the Abominable Snow Plow in Monster Trucks Inc, and the P.T. Flea car... Mack suddenly realizes all of these characters are voiced by the same actor and says, "Wait a minute here... they're just using the same actor over and over! What kind of a cut-rate production is this?!"

Circus Cab has a heavy-duty plastic face on a die-cast body, and we've really come to appreciate the durability of these models over the years. You'll need to open your wallet a lot wider for these models, with their premium prices, since your chances of finding them at the retail level are slim-to-none. Suggest doing some shopping/monitoring of prices before plunking down what's always a big chunk of change for these models, but we're betting (and hoping!) that these will increase in value over the years, and that the grandkids can either hang on to these collectors models or sell them for a pretty penny (if they're still even MAKING pennies when that time comes!) We'll be collecting all of these new Super Chase models for our middle grandson, having already rounded up the previous ones for our older grandson (2011's Frosty, Flash Long Ge, Memo Rojas & Russian Racer Vitaly Petrov, 2012's Hiroaki, Takeshi & Yukio, and 2014's "95" Fans Luigi & Guido, "Ciao" Francesco Bernoulli, Trike Feldman, and Carateka.)

(1/16/15 update: We did end up purchasing this from Amazon in December 2015 for $10.99... obviously didn't wait long enough, since it's on Amazon today for $9.99! Not a good sign for collectors when the prices of a Super Chase model goes DOWN!)hese models, with their premium prices, since your chances of finding them at the retail level are slim-to-none. Suggest doing some shopping/monitoring of prices before plunking down what's always a big chunk of change for these models, but we're betting (and hoping!) that these will increase in value over the years, and that the grandkids can either hang on to these collectors models or sell them for a pretty penny (if they're still even MAKING pennies when that time comes!) We'll be collecting all of these new Super Chase models for our middle grandson, having already rounded up the previous ones for our older grandson (2011's Frosty, Flash Long Ge, Memo Rojas & Russian Racer Vitaly Petrov, 2012's Hiroaki, Takeshi & Yukio, and 2014's "95" Fans Luigi & Guido, "Ciao" Francesco Bernoulli, Trike Feldman, and Carateka.) (1/16/15 update: We did end up purchasing this from Amazon in December 2015 for $10.99... obviously didn't wait long enough, since it's on Amazon today for $9.99! Not a good sign for collectors when the prices of a Super Chase model goes DOWN!)

product_title: Melissa & Doug Water Wow Coloring Book - Vehicles
review_headline: The pictures and brush are great. But
review_body: The pictures and brush are great.  But, it should not be in a spiral form.  For several reasons. First..2 kids cannot share at the same time...one could use a paint brush and water...but can't because they are bound together.  Takes FOREVER TO DRY again because they are bound together.  I ended up cutting the spiral off so I would have loose pages that can be shared and dry easily.  Instead of a spiral.  They should have a single hole punch in the top left corner.  Use a plastic reclisable ring to hold the pages together after they are dry or for transporting.  Otherwise it is sweet.  My 5 and 3 year old grand boys love the pictures and the water brush.  No mess.  Fun activity.  Mimi

product_title: Disney Sofia The First Royal Tea Party Giftset
review_headline: Confirming the Other Reviews of Quality and Design
review_body: I gave this to my child and the recent reviews are spot on that mention heads pop off and the figures will not sit in the chairs.  The plastic of the dolls' dresses is a very smooth texture and so there is no friction to keep them in the seats.  I personally tried over and over and I would equate the challenge of keeping the dolls seated to that of erecting a house of cards.  It is not something most adults could accomplish.  My daughter is so in love with all thing Sofia and the items in this set appear to conform to the scale of the other toys for sale so it has some value as part of an overall collection.  Virtually all Sofia toys come with a new Sofia doll, so my daughter already has many.  I simply would not buy this toy if the recipient child does not already have a collection of Sofia toys.  On its own, this toy is only going to be a frustrating waste of money.

product_title: Innovation
review_headline: Great game, good mix of strategy and luck
review_body:
I very much like this game. I have a short attention span and have no patience for a game that takes too long to learn. I like simple games with simple rules that have deep strategies that become apparent the more you play and this game does not disappoint.

One of the things that I like is that things change all the time, and sometimes dramatically, the person who has been ahead for the entire game now is the loser and the person the furthest behind is suddenly the leader. Good strategy game with cards that provide enough randomness that you will be kept guessing.

One of my favorites.

review_headline: Smaller from what I remember but still great!
review_body: Had the old school purple and yellow one years ago as a kid and when I saw this on amazon I knew I had to buy one. I had hours of fun with the as a kid and have always been a fan of Nerf products because they are usually well made and safe for children like my son to use. Of course it arrived in a timely manner and when I opened it the smell of the Nerf ball was exactly the same as when I was younger. Awesome product to throw around on the beach and it floats which is full proof for kids. Only two cons I can really see which aren't completely bad anyway is that it's alot smaller then I remember so when adults like me with huge hands throw it it strains your arm because it's so light and small. Secondly it doesn't whistle as loud as the one I had as a kid. But aside from that great product brought back alot of memories throwing it around with friends and my son.

product_title: Bite Coin - Bite Out Quarter Magic Coin by Roy Kueppers
review_headline: It looks and works great. Five stars for functionality
review_body: It looks and works great.  Five stars for functionality.  The problem is that the one I got is a Montana state quarter, so I had to hunt for a quarter that matches it in order to make a convincing switch.  Would be a better product if it were simply a basic quarter.  In fact, it never occurred to me until this arrived that the U.S. Mint putting out all those state quarters makes using this gimmick a bit dicey, as you can no longer ask for a member of your audience to produce a quarter of their own for the switch: the chance of their quarter not matching your gimmick quarter is too likely...

product_title: Terra Mystica Board Game
review_body: The mechanics are simple and familiar to veteran board game players, but numerous enough that getting up to speed for the first play takes a while.  Investing time to learn pays off, though, as the complexity of the strategy and the variability of each game provide an incredible experience every time.  This one is a real workout for your brain - strategy purists looking to weed out the luck factor of dice and random draws won't find a more rewarding game.  From the very start, the impact of every decision you make is felt throughout the rest of the game.

product_title: RX Aerio® Micro Mini Nano Drone - The World's Smallest Quadcopter with 4CH 2.4GHz 6-Axis Gyro LED Lights RC Remote Control Helicoptor Quadcopter
review_headline: Fun to fly, not easy to control.
review_body: Yes, it is fun but but it is very slow on the response time. Flying in the house it doesn't respond well to the controls. I can't get it to hover in one spot. When I throttle up the power it takes off and hits the ceiling if you don't pull back on the throttle, but then it drops like a rock to the floor. I broke one blade on my first flight. No idea where to get anymore other then the extras that came with the unit. Range is not what they said. Thirty meters is 98 feet but outside flying going straight up about as high as my single story house it shuts off and drops like a stone. Flying vertically it won't make it to first base from home plate before dropping. Charging from my car charger, it takes 20-30 minutes for about 5 minutes of flying time. Give or take. I get longer because it takes me time to go and turn it back over. If I could keep it in the air the whole time it would fly five minutes. Trim buttons don't seem to work.

product_title: Find It Games on the Go Things that Go
review_body:
Find It To Go Things That Go. These Find It Games To Go are limited Quantity. These to go editions are half the size of the normal ones. Perfect to throw into a travel bag or keep in the car for road trips. This a contained game, so no chances of losing pieces. Every time someone comes to our house, they notice the Find it games we have. It never fails, they end up playing them while hanging out. They are fun for all ages!Adults get more competitive than the kids… Well, at least the ones we know.

You can play a few different ways. You can play solo or compete with a friend. You can time yourself to see how fast you can find the items, or see if you can find them in alphabet order. You can also make stories with the items you find. Don’t forget to look out for the mystery item! Need help keeping track of what you have found or what is on the list? product_title: Leray Self Balancing Scooter Balance Motion 6.5" Two Wheel Hoverboard with Certified Safe Battery Pack (Black)
review_body:
[[VIDEOID:164d1b12ad70bf7050a19c925291a025]]First off, let me say that this scooter is F*U*N!!! As you can see in the video I go from never having seen one to riding it comfortably in ten minutes. The hardest part about learning to ride it was that all the neighbor kids wanted a turn! I really was enjoying it until I was able to get it above a few miles an hour, then I felt the slight rub on the right wheel that became worse at increased speeds. Then after charging it a second time I began to have issues with the battery. Every time I rode for more than five minutes the red battery light started blinking and the warning alarm buzzed. I'd recharge it then try to ride it but then it started buzzing after riding it for three minutes. So I contacted the Leray people through the warranty card in the box: they immediately emailed me a return UPS label and as soon as they received my scooter they sent me a new one. Seamless.

The new one works fine: it charged up in under an hour and I rode for an hour this afternoon. It's really addictive! If you want to have some fun, I highly recommend getting one these scooters.

PS - Writing reviews has become an accidental hobby for me, and it always makes my day to know that people find my reviews helpful (and if not, why.) Also, if you have any questions, clarifications, or comments please feel free to leave a comment below. I usually respond pretty quickly and almost always within 24 hours. This item was provided for review consideration.

Cheers! Clairey and almost always within 24 hours. This item was provided for review consideration. Cheers! Claire

product_title: Hess 1999 Toy Truck and Space Shuttle with Satellite
review_headline: Got it going... After some work!
review_body:
So I bought this truck despite all the negative reviews... What the heck it looks great and I figured I could deal with whatever. And this was true as the model, despite being advertised with no batteries included, it had the 2 of 3 sets of batteries with, and yes they were corroded, especially in the truck itself. Nothing fatal, but I had to perform some work to restore all three items, truck, space shuttle and satellite to fine working order.
The good news is that Hess does a great job of screwing everything together, so things come apart pretty easily.
Here's what I had to do.
1. Take out and dispose of batteries from the truck and satellite.
2. Clean acid build up from the terminals
3. Use wet or dry 400 grit sandpaper to scrub off the remaining corrosion on the terminals
4. Take apart truck body, not cab (careful, one of the taillight lenses came out along with the rear bumper. And I accidentally dislodged one wire)
5. Clean inside terminals.
6. Solder any loose wires on... Use heat sink to prevent plastic melting.
7. Insert batteries and test lights with top of truck body off. They did not work for me! I then noticed that the positive and negative terminals of one side of the battery's contacts Needed to be connected by a wire, but no wire was attached! (Could of corroded off, but I didn't see it in the truck body.... Go figure... So I took a wire and connected these two terminals together and wallah! The lights all worked on the truck.
8. Screw all back together
9. Clean all battery compartments for residual acidic leakage.
10. Install batteries in all 3 items, testing as you go.
It took a couple of hours in total, including getting tools, firing off the soldering iron, getting new batteries and cleaning up.
Today I Skyped with my 4 yo a grandson and showed him the truck etc ( He has a 2014 Hess truck set I got him at his home in AZ.). He was pumped. He scrambled out to get his truckand we compared the toys, firing off lights, sounds etc. he really got pumped when the satellite came out. So this is now his truck for when he visits.
All in things worked out. Shouldn't have to do out that, but didn't actually mind that much. Seller should fix the ad and take out all the three types of batteries... And lower the cost due to corrosion damage.

product_title: Dohdles! What is that?!
review_headline: Fun, challenging, creative and hands on, this is a great game
review_body: I'll bet that Dohdles! becomes one of the most popular games this year because it comes in a square box, has a tempting graphic, is geared to older kids and most adults, consists of several components, and it is great fun.  My family members are bread bakers and artists and we like to be challenged.  After a tasty dinner and some beverages, we clear the table and jump in to this game that can surprise us as the scoring progresses.  Being that the dohdler or the dohdlees can all score, anything can happen.  Playing the game with a group that did not know each other well got off to a slower start, but once the testing of boundaries moved into the fine line between too obvious a sculpture and the obscure creation, we were entertained over the period of more than an hour.  Since the dough is reused, I insisted that all hands be washed prior to playing and nobody minded once they realized my motivation.  I expect that I will eventually be purchasing a replacement dough, though.

Find It To Go Pet Finder. These Find It Games To Go are limited Quantity. These to go editions are half the size of the normal ones. Perfect to throw into a travel bag or keep in the car for road trips. This a contained game, so no chances of losing pieces. Every time someone comes to our house, they notice the Find it games we have. It never fails, they end up playing them while hanging out. They are fun for all ages! Adults get more competitive than the kids… Well, at least the ones we know.

product_title: Terrace Houses - Type 2 (Pre-Painted)
review_body:
I love this item. It came in a pre-cut flat pack of punch-out wood-composite pieces. All of the pieces are pre-painted as described / pictured. It took maybe 30-60 minutes of very easy assembly. The design/assembly seems very well thought out. The walls are double-layered to provide some extra integrity.

I love that the windows are cut-out to allow you to see in/through, unlike Battlefront resin houses... it may not make a difference in play, because you still can't identify units through the tiny windows, but it is a nice touch.

The roof can be removed in three separate pieces. The second floor can be removed as one piece. There are tiny pegs / holes to align / steady the second floor on the first floor; I can see those pegs getting destroyed with frequent use, but haven't experienced that yet.

product_title: Little Adventures Cape & Sword Costume Sets for Boys
review_headline: The sword is in the trash and the cape isn't being worn.  Here are the issues....
review_body:
I have an average sized 4 year old. When he saw this set he was pretty excited. However, the excitement did not last long. Here are the issues:

Sword: the sword is hard foam. Which is good for not causing damage. However, the sword broke in half at the base of the blade/top of the handle after a couple of days of use. We tried gluing it, but it didn't hold.

Cape: it is a bit too tight at the neck. There is maybe an inch or two of play. Which is not that much for a kid running around. He excitedly put it on the first time, thought it was too tight and hasn't worn it since.

Sum: If you are giving this to a boy with a thin neck that is very gentle with toys - then this is a great set. However, for the rest of the boys out there, it would be better if the neck was an inch or two bigger and maybe if there was a more solid layer under the foam to keep the sword from breaking easily. I hope this is helpful to you!

product_title: The Learning Journey Techno Gears Marble Mania Zoomerang Building Kit
review_headline: Twin Tested And Approved For Fun, Be Prepared To Help
review_body: I'd agreed that a couple of little eight year old special someones could stay up until they got this constructed, so I thought that I was being played when two hours came and went and it was still in pieces. It was my night to be "off," so it fell to my spouse to bring it to an end. Using his own kid friendly profanity (snuggerfuts!) and infinite patience, he was able to help them get the various scattered bits assembled into a final product. The problem was one of strength; some pieces required real muscle power in order to achieve a full connection. Play finally began after a few test runs identified which tracks needed additional adjustments. They barely played an hour before being done with it for the night. The next morning they had another hour before their mother picked them up and they spent every possible minute with it until they left. It waits for them on the dining room table and I notice it wobbles a lot when I pass by. I spoke to T2 (twin two) this morning and asked if he loved it or liked it (like) and if there was anything people buying this should know; he said to say that it needs more marbles. In short, this [[ASIN:B00TXNJ45M The Learning Journey Techno Gears Marble Mania Zoomerang Building Kit (100-Piece), Multi]] may require adult assistance to put together and, if you buy it, you should consider buying extra marbles too. Any toy that can inspire hours of play is a plus in my  book.

product_title: Fisher-Price Nickelodeon Blaze and the Monster Machines Super Stunts Blaze
review_headline: Lots of fun if you have lots of room.
review_body:
This toy is a knock-it-out-of-the-park hit. Sure, the toy is, as one reviewer noted, "limited play." The "limited" part is that it does five things, and requires a ton of room, like a family room or a really big outdoor area. Blaze does not work well on carpeting. Though Blaze "only" does five things, periodically you get cued to give Blaze a hand, like filling his tires or revving his engine.

Blaze is surprisingly heavy, but the weight is needed to help Blaze do his multiple stunts. A lever automatically lowers to help Blaze do his various stunts. Technically, Blaze only does five things, four of which are stunts, but Blaze seems to do a bit of ad-libbing from time to time that makes the five stunts seem like a lot more. Blaze lifts up from the back, from the front, from the side, and does tail spins. Blaze also talks and provides his own music. Admittedly, the talking and music can get a little old, but it is so amusing to watch Blaze do tricks that we had little time to be bored.

The only "down side" to Blaze is that Blaze requires a LOT of area without carpeting to do his stunts. Blaze does have a power mode that works okay on carpet, but any stunts that use the automatic lever work much better on a relatively smooth surface, like a concrete or hardwood floor.

We have had many different toy vehicles over the decades, some of which were nearly the cost of this vehicle. Many of those vehicles only did one thing. Occasionally they might do something else, like pop a wheelie. But none of those vehicles would do all the things this vehicle will do. Frankly, I would have loved this toy as a child. What the heck, I love this toy as an adult. Then there are the grandchildren, if they can get it away from grandpa.

Enjoy!

product_title: Nature Bound Bug Catcher Toy, Eco-Friendly Bug Vacuum, Catch and Release Indoor/Outdoor Play, Ages 5-12
review_body:
While I shudder at the thought of playing with nasty creepy crawlers now, I can remember as a young boy being fascinated with whatever I managed to dig up, scoop up, catch in a jar, etc. etc. From spiders to worms, toads to lightning bugs, things "in the wild" were part of my little world. Of course I didn't have anything cool like this set, but boy I wish I did, and I imagine any youngster of those magical years would be all over this.

To foster a potential interest in biology & life sciences, this is a decent start. Consider purchasing the set which comes with the critter barn- [[ASIN:B00UUS460C Nature Bound Bug Vacuum and Critter Barn Habitat Combo Set]].

product_title: Lil Monkey Dome Climber, Multicolor
review_headline: The Lil Monkey Playground Deserves 5 Stars (But we Dislike the App)
review_body:
My family uses the Lil Monkey Playground Jungle Gym Monkey Bar in our home daily. We have setup the Jungle Gym in our living room so our son with ASD can use it anytime he wants. For OT purposes, we place a crash pad under the unit and my son climbs to the top and drops down onto his crash pad from the top/middle opening.

Note: My children who use the Gym are 1, 3, and 5.

My five and three year-old children are able to use the Gym at the same time without it disconnecting from the floor. On occasion, if my five year-old jerks the unit intentionally, he can make one side bounce but this is an intentional act on his part and the gym doesn't move more than a centimeter before returning to the floor. (They offer ground anchors that are sold separately if this is a concern for someone.)

My 1 year old walks around the outside of the gym and swings from the lowest bar -- he loves it.

All of my children enjoy their time climbing on the gym unit.

--

In regards to the application that accompanies this product... this is why I haven't provided a perfect score. The application that is offered to be used with the Lil Monkey Playground Jungle Gym doesn't promote the child actually using the Gym. The child can use the app by sitting away from the gym, alone with their tablet, and pointing the tablet's camera at the Gym. I don't understand how this promotes actual use of the Gym and I believe the app hinders the overall "get active" goal. I wish I could rate these two items separately. If I could, the Gym itself would receive a perfect, 5 stars, and the app would receive only 1.

product_title: Air Swimmers Remote Control Flying Shark
review_body:
As an R/C pilot for over 20 years I have lots of fun with this. Several things to consider based on the non sense comments made from some really uninformed buyers.

1. This is based on a balloon. Do you really expect it to take abuse? C'mon man
2. This is based on a balloon filled with helium. You take it outside and it either flies away or doesn't stay put. Really?

This is a novelty item for indoor use only and not a high end R/C aircraft. My kid loves it and my office mates get a kick out of flying past their cubes. If you want high end R/C then you are in the wrong section. With this said I love mine and when I break it, i'll buy the replacement balloon and keep it flying.

product_title: VTech Flipsies Sandy's House and Ocean Cruiser Doll House
review_headline: This is a super interactive toy that keeps her entertained for hours
review_body:
My almost six year old daughter just discovered Flipsies and absolutely adores Sandy’s House & Ocean Cruiser!

This is a super interactive toy that keeps her entertained for hours. There are lots of things for Sandy and her little pink dolphin friend to do – drive the boat, ride the zip line, eat a turkey dinner, go down the water slide, splash in the pool, take a bath and even go to bed.

Each area on the Ocean Cruiser has a sensor and when Sandy touches it, she talks specifically about being in that area – with multiple phrases for each area. You never knew what she was going to say!

Sandy comes with multiple outfits and hairdos so that she can transform her look depending on what kind of play your child is having with her. The boat also flips up so children can play with Sand both outside and inside the boat.

Sandy’s House & Ocean Cruiser was easy to put together – all I had to do was just snap pieces into place. There is also a detailed diagram for all the decals. It took about 7 minutes in total to prep for my daughter.

What I really like about this set is how it stimulates my daughter’s imaginative play. It’s also great that Sandy is a Marine Biologist, talking about dolphins and even a whale – she will definitely inspire girls to go into science and into careers that helps others.

“The product has been provided by VTech so you could experience it with your family; however, the thoughts and opinions are all your own.”

review_headline: The Hobbytown store I bought it at said too bad, call the manufacturer

product_title: VTech Count and Learn Alphabet Bus
review_headline: VERY loud and doesn't turn down far enough; and volume is too easy for child to turn back up!
review_body:
The way it works, the appeal to the toddlers and preschoolers in the house... all this is great. What I took off stars for is that it's OBNOXIOUS. Really loud; and you can turn it down but it's still loud... and on top of it the sound buttons are right where the kids play and are easy to push; so they turn it right back up to REALLY, REALLY, REALLY loud even if you turn it down.

It's also not designed great as far as educationally. The letters and numbers fit in but they only go in one way; so unless the child knows that it's not upside down, it won't fit. This was frustrating for my toddler; and in all reality, it's basically an expensive pushing bus with little pieces to sort.

Now if you don't mind any of that, then the educational aspects are great. If you are willing to sit with your child and do it with him they would totally love it and you could help them. It has several different games, phonics, letter recognition,music... just a blast if you don't mind it literally blasting at you. LOL

product_title: LeapFrog LeapTV: Disney Frozen: Arendelle's Winter Festival Educational
review_body:
When this arrived in the mail there were squeals of delight from my 5 year old twins!

This game is designed for 4-7 year-olds, but I suspect that it is better suited for 4-6 year-olds.

There are several mini-games available to choose from within this winter festival. One of my girls preferred the ice skating game that asks players to put numbers in the proper sequence, and then Anna or Elsa skates along the pattern. Both girls loved helping Anna and Elsa to leap and turn.

My other daughter loved the ice sculpting mini-game. She enjoyed seeing the geometric shapes morph into the sculptures.

All in all, this is a fun and educational game. I am enjoying seeing the girls "level up" and watching the game adjust for their individual strengths.

My older, gamer, sons like to point out that the game is not overly sophisticated. But I point out that this is a system built from the ground up for kids their sisters' age, and not an adult console made to work for younger kids.

I would prefer a faster processing speed, but I think that is my adult impatience shining through.

Disclosure: I was provided a copy of this game in order to facilitate my review. However, all opinions are 100% my own and I was not required to give a positive review.

Of course I didn't have anything cool like this set, but boy I wish I did, and I imagine any youngster of those magical years would be all over this. review_headline: Avoid deleting a password entry, edit instead. Otherwise love it!

If you delete an entry it is very likely that you will also delete an entry near it without being aware that you have.  After buying this device for myself and five of my family members, I sadly experienced the loss of my credit union password info ( this being my only bank) while deleting a Master Card password.  Both entries started with MA. I read other reviews on Amazon then and found others have had this happen to them.  I still love my password vault but will caution my family members to only edit entries, never delete.

product_title: Cars 2 Animated Talking Alarm Clock
review_headline: Cute but not efficient as alarm clock.
review_body:
First, my 5 yr old loves the different animated talking McQueen (different sounds for about 5 seconds each time) when snooze button was pressed at "press and try" while the clock was still in its packaging. But when we actually tried to use it as an 'Alarm' clock, it has the McQueen animated talking sound as alarm as intended, but guess what, that sound only lasted approx 5 seconds and then the alarm shuts off on its own. Which is useless to us because 5 seconds of animated talking did nothing to wake my child up.

I was hoping the clock would have all those included different animated talking sounds repeated continuously until 'snooze' button was pushed to snooze it and repeat again after 10 mnts or so, like normal alarm clock does. Unfortunately, this clock only make ONE 5-second animated sound (and it's not loud at all) and shuts off. At this point, even a regular beeping alarm clock would work better, at least it will keep beeping until it's snoozed or turned off manually.
Other than that, the clock is cute and attractive, thus the 2 stars. Too bad it's not an efficient actual alarm clock, or it would have been perfect for my son who loves cars.

product_title: Sanwa JLF-TP-8YT-SK OEM Vermilion Ball Handle Arcade Joystick 4 & 8 Way Adjustable from Sanwa
review_headline: Really is an arcade quality product.
review_body:
It's durable, hefty and it looks good. It plays well too. and it comes with everything you need to install it.

Of course, it's designed around a square restrictor gate. It even comes with one. So if you are like me, and prefer the feel of an octagonal restrictor gate, there's going to be a learning curve. When you switch gates like that, you end up losing roughly half of the diagonal sensitivity, because of the way the microswitches are placed. So while you have a smoother overall motion, you need to be very deliberate in hitting all of the directions.

Now this isn't a knock against the joystick, even though it may seem like it. This is more of a warning to anyone who might be thinking of switching the gate out. And even then, the replacement gates are pretty cheap, and take about 20 seconds to install. I'm still quite happy I put one of these in my arcade stick, because they feel great to use, and it contrasts well with my black case.

So as far as I'm concerned, this is the best joystick I've used. Just maybe do some research if you want to swap out restrictor gates on it.

product_title: Smash Up: Science Fiction Double Feature Expansion
review_headline: More decks for added contradictory confusion!
review_body: This game can be fun if you have friends that like to nerd it out and argue over ambiguous definitions of words in the rules/on the cards, but it can be fairly confusing keeping track of which actions/abilities take effect at what time... for example, certain minions' ability say if they get "destroyed" then something happens, but the rules don't explicitly state what qualifies as "destroyed"- is it any time they go to the discard pile (per another card's action, or when a base scores), is it only when the action explicitly says "destroy this minion", or does it also include when they "go back into the owner's hand" per another action card/minion ability? It's fun to see how different pairs of decks mesh, but some overpower others, and different combinations of rules make some cards completely useless. Players who haven't played Smash Up before are in for some confusion the first couple rounds, but if you're not in it for competition but just to see what happens, it'll work out.

product_title: Square Shooters The first deck of cards on dice
review_headline: Novel and practical at the same time
review_body:
It's tough to convey the amount of game design and gameplay potential that's in this. If you like chucking dice, card games adapted to other mediums, or combination dice+card games, this is your sandbox.
Nice, large, well-engraved/painted dice. Goal cards are tiny, but they're only goal cards - nobody really handles the cards that much. Score chips are passable.
These dice are made to fulfill Poker and Rummy requirements. If you roll all 9, you will get a decent-to-outstanding hand with every roll. They're great game-design tools, the normal game is great, adaptations of other card games I've played on these were great. Basically, greatness.

EDIT: Over a year later, this is still my most-played dice game. I own two sets now (engraved one set with a dot to tell them apart) and have adapted Canasta to the dice. People love it! The dice are my favorite dice, and have been since I got them. The engravings and printing on them are top-notch and don't wear away. This is one of two dice games whose dice I consider to be of heirloom quality - suitable for just about anyone who appreciates this sort of thing. The inclusion of the Jokers does necessitate some rules to deal with them (for games that don't use them), but beyond that, you'll never run out of new ways to play with these. I have a LOT of dice that take after card decks, and these have the most effort put into their design and workmanship.

product_title: Little Tikes Princess  Cozy Coupe - 30th Anniversary
review_body:
My granddaughter loves her Cozy Coup. I was so excited when my daughter got this for her daughter - as I have many fond memories of both of my children playing with their cozy coup's when they were toddlers. The design hasn't changed a lot in the over 25 years since my kids had these - I guess if something isn't broke, don't fix it. One nice feature about the newer models is they are taller and I am able to push my 18 month old granddaughter in her "car" without it breaking my back. I am only 5'5" and I think anyone much taller then me would have to bend though.

I put the coup together and used the on-line video instruction and it made the job very easy. I did it by myself and had no issues. I am a visual person so this was much better than the instruction manual. Following the video step-by-step will assure you don't put anything together bassackwards .... you do not want to try and take this baby apart believe me. After I put it together we took it for a few spins in the house on the hardwood floors and one of the front wheels did not operate properly - it was kind of "frozen" and wouldn't swivel like it should. I called Little Tikes and their rep was very friendly and helpful. Once we took it outside on the concrete it worked perfectly. Couldn't get the necessary traction inside (probably not an ideal inside toy anyway but with grandparents, we have a whole different set of rules than we did for our own kids lol!) .

Get one of these for your kids or grandkids - they will love it - and so will you.

product_title: Water Balloons Bulk FabQuality(TM) 111 Balloons Per Minute FREE Water Games eBook! 100 Water Balloons in One Minute As Seen on TV Products for Children 111 Self Sealing Balloons 60 Seconds
review_body:
[[VIDEOID:8995a879ace10f830f08bed963d66b70]] Such Fun!!! Ever since the video went viral on the internet earlier this summer of this awesome gadget I have been wanting to try it. When I was offered a chance to review this item at a discounted price in exchange for my honest, unbiased review I jumped at the chance!!

The only possible way to show you how easy and cool the Bunch On Balloons pack is - is to show you first hand. I decided to video the entire process of setting it up for the first time. Being so excited to try this, I barely skimmed the directions. It seemed simple enough as the balloons are attatched to the bottom of skinny straws with a hose bracket on the top that will easily attach to your hose. Simply attach the bunch to the hose and fill with the balloons on the ground, once you see they are at full capacity they will start to fall off on their own and you do a little jiggle to shake the rest off.

The reason I am giving 4 stars instead of 5 is only because there was one or two balloons that were ripped and another balloon was still squirting out water from the top tie once it was released from the straws. But considering just how many balloons you get in this bunch I didn't mind at all.

A bonus is, they email you a pdf of a bunch of games to play with the balloons, that is if you choose to not just throw them at any moving and non moving objects as soon as they are done filling. :)

product_title: OgoSport OgoBild Animate It Studio Kit with Webcam
review_headline: Not bad, but we think the Hue animation kit is better (comparision)
review_body:
cWe've had the Hue animation kit for a couple of years now and have really loved it [[ASIN:B0049TTKEU HUE Animation Studio (Red) for Windows PCs and Apple Mac OS X: complete stop motion animation kit with camera, software and book]] , so we were excited to give this new kit a go, curious to see if it had any added features or benefits. Unfortunately we've been disappointed with it.

1. The camera is definitely of lower quality, It does not have a weighted base but instead a suction cup, and the head of the camera (the end where all the functional stuff is and the lens) is much heavier, so it's quite top heavy. The suction cup is not a good idea as it doesn't make up for a weighted base, especially since it doesn't stick to many surfaces. We've not had any issues with the Hue camera falling over and luckily it does not have a suction cup, but the Animate it camera cannot stand on it's own and must be suction attached to something. The quality of the images the camera in this Animate it kit produces are not clear. The Hue camera can be focused directly by turning the lens, and while the camera on this kit has a lens that turns as well, we were not able to get it very clear. It is interesting to note that on the Animate it website & Amazon page the image of the lens shows information written on the ring of the lens stating it's resolution and zoom, however, the camera in the kit does not have any of this printed information. I don't know if that indicates this has a different camera/lens or not, but it's definitely a poor quality one. The Hue camera also has a speaker built into the camera, so if you are doing audio voice over you're all set with the camera/microphone all-in-one.

2. This Animate it kit comes with little plastic doo-hickeys (the OgoSport/OgoBild things) that you can create little creatures with as the subject of your animation. My daughter was not at all interested in these, preferring instead to use clay (our Hue kit from a couple years ago came with clay, but the newer ones seem not to anymore, and instead include a klutz animation book). This is just personal preference, but something to note. It seems to me that these plastic things might appeal to younger kids? My daughter is 11.

3. The software, while adequate for most kids, isn't as comprehensive as the Hue animation software. It also doesn't have as good of instructions (video instructions for the Hue are really great and make each step to make animations very easy to figure out and do). My daughter was 8 when we first used the Hue kit and I did have to help her with some activities, especially some editing and splicing in music so the fade ins and outs were right where we wanted them, but once she got going she was very independent in creating her films.

Some folks have mentioned that they don't feel the software with this Animate it kit is limited (it's called animate it express because it has less features than their fully fledged Animate it software) However, it doesn't offer all the features you can do on the Hue software, esp. related to editing, splicing in music, having different audio tracks, etc. It's just much more basic. Many kids may be happy with the more basic software, but once you've had more control and options for your animations it's hard to give some of that up.

4. Price - the price of this kit is definitely less than the Hue kit, but also bear in mind that the Hue has a longer history and has won all kinds of awards, is used in schools, and overall has a much better camera and full featured software. I think if your kid is 10+, and/or really into animation they'll be much happier with the Hue kit. Younger kids may be just fine with this kit (although the camera will frustrate you no matter what your age).

SUMMARY: Based on our experience with both this kit and the HUE kit, the HUE is the clear winner for overall quality and features (and I think for learning to use it, but that's subjective and others may feel the software for this Animate it kit is just as easy)ut that's subjective and others may feel the software for this Animate it kit is just as easy)

product_title: Scrabble Tiles - 100pc Plastic Black Tiles - Perfect For Crafting and Scrapbooking
review_headline: Scrabble Tiles Black Plastic Pro Grade Tiles - Great for Craft Projects
review_body:
The lettered side of the Scrabble Black Plastic Pro Grade Tiles is perfectly smooth, so there is no way to "feel out" a letter or blank if you're picking them from a bag. They also shuffle around well, if you're sliding them around on a flat surface or in the box top. I like the holes in the back of the tiles, it makes them easy to grip and move them around easier.

While we're not big game players around here, we are big time crafters. Just a few months ago, we were looking around for some old Scrabble games, but couldn't find any. I had no idea we could buy just the tiles! Imagine my excitement when we found the Scrabble Tiles made by Max Tiles. We settled on the black tiles to make graduation picture frames, since my daughter recently graduated from high school. Her school colors were orange and black and these tiles are perfect!

I can't wait to order more of the Max Tiles Scrabble Tiles in other colors.

Disclosure: I was provided with a free or discounted product in order to review this item. However, this did not influence my review. All opinions are true and my own.

review_headline: ok, but not as intuitive as such a simple game should be

product_title: Nerf Zombie Strike Hammershot Blaster
review_body:
My 9-year old son went to Target with $18 burning a hole in his pocket and he picked out this Nerf blaster.
I wasn't sure how well the gun would shoot since it's only cocked using a hammer (like you'd see on a cowboy gun), but it provides plenty of power.
Cocking the hammer can be done easily one-handed and even my son (or 7-year old daughter) has no problems with it.
It has a paint scheme that gives it that "zombie" feel and the grip itself feels good in the hand.

I'll admit, I wasn't sold on the idea of cocking it using the hammer, but it's very easy to do one handed and if you had another one of these guns you could easily go Akimbo (dual-wield).
What I thought would make this gun not so fun to shoot has turned into the thing that I like most about it.....the cocking hammer.

This is a great Nerf gun...5 shots that can be unleashed one-handed. What's not to love?

product_title: Masterpieces French Riviera Signature Series Jigsaw Puzzle
review_body: Everything about the puzzle is great except for one thing.  There are at least half a dozen places where the die cuts for a piece's protruding knob was offset so close to a side that the 'shoulder' of the piece was only conneced by a very thin neck or was cut off of the piece completely.  Now all the 'fragments' created by this poor die cutting were in the plastic bag of puzzle pieces and if you really tried you could a) find them in the 'chaff' and 2) carefully insert them into the puzzle. Even if you did, it is obvious to a puzzle person (me!) that the resulting surface is flawed.  Overall, poor quality control in the die cutting process results in a less than perfect puzzle.

product_title: Pokémon Trading Card Game: XY — Roaring Skies Sealed Elite Trainer Box
review_headline: This was the perfect gift for my niece that just got interested in ...
review_body: This was the perfect gift for my niece that just got interested in the Pokemon card game and already has a few decks.  If you already have a deck this kit includes everything else you'll need to play a full game (damage counters, dice, rule book).  I remember when I was a kid how much I loved opening a new pack and seeing what was inside.  We opened a few of the packs when I gave them to her and each one had a hologram card inside!  In the 5 packs we opened we found one EX card, which I guess is a big deal, and a few common and uncommon foil cards.  This is a great gift for a kid that likes Pokemon, and the box will keep it all organized so mom and dad aren't getting in trouble for stepping on the cards.

product_title: NECA Iron Maiden Clothed 8" Figure Piece of Mind Action Figure
review_body:
Iron Maiden has always featured Eddie "The Head" on all of their album artwork, as well as in their stage performances. This particular Eddie is represented on the album Piece of Mind.

I've never owned one of the new NECA mego styled figures, so I had no idea what to expect. I'm glad I got this one, he is quite an awesome figure.

The sculpt of his head is a dead on representation of the album artwork, and the face is scary as it should be. Every detail was paid attention too, down to the tiny screws holding the plate that holds his head together. This is one of the best head sculpts I have ever seen on an action figure. The feet are sculpted equally grotesque, and they look appropriately Eddie. From the knee up, however, he is a plain, flesh toned "buck" body. His collar around his neck is very well sculpted as well, straight down to the tiny little lock that looks as though it holds it shut. It even features real metal chains attached to it.

Paint on Eddie is fantastic. The face is so detailed that Eddie appears to have crawled right out of the album artwork. His teeth, tongue, eyes, and even the bit of blood dripping from his skull cap are expertly applied. The only thing that costs this figure points on paint is that NECA have decided to "shade" the head and collar like on the album artwork, and not on the clothes, so he looks to be half shaded. Even with the jarring paint shading on his head and collar, he is still an amazing portrayal of Eddie.

The cloth clothes are very nice, in my opinion. His jeans are appropriately ripped and have been "stained" to appear dirty. The straightjacket is amazing, and has lots of straps on the back as it should. Both the pants and straightjacket have Velcro on them, and while the pants are easily removed, I can not see any way to take the straightjacket off without damaging it. Looks like Eddie is permanently restrained.

The articulation on Eddie is pretty good too. He has a double ball jointed head/neck that allows a nice range of motion, though it is a little tight. His legs have hinged hips, swivel thighs, hinged knees, and hinged ankles. The legs allow a nice range of motion, however it does feel slightly limited due to the cloth jeans. The upper body has a waist swivel, and the arms are as articulated as the legs. The straightjacket however prevents most motion though, and while his arms are slightly movable, they will never have the range of articulation that other figures have.

Overall, this NECA mego styled Eddie, from the classic Iron Maiden album Piece of Mind, is a must have for fans of the band and these NECA figures. Highly reccomended.

She told me to think of the ones used for golf.  When I switched her to them, I did notice an improvement with her writing.  One day, while I was casually browsing Crayola product on Amazon, I came across these. I was so excited that I immideately purchased them for my daughter (and I) to use.  She loves them, as do I.  She can finally color without breaking the tool she is using, which happens with her and crayons frequently. This set has every color you need, and a convienent built in sharpener.  Really just everything you need.  I loves these so much that I plan on buying her a second set for Christmas.

We especially loved how you unlock new dresses and accessories and hairstyles and then you can take your picture wearing those.  It really made her feel like a princess.  It's also nice that some of the games are body interactive, to get your child moving but it's also easier for the little ones to do than using the controller but sometimes they motion is a little too sensitive and causes them to get an answer wrong accidentally.  There are lots of games within this cartridge and well worth it.

product_title: Flutterbye- Fairy Princess
review_body: I have a 6 year old daughter who adores this fairy and would easily give it 5 stars. She loves everything about it. However, as a parent, I have some concerns. It is a lot of fun once you get her in the air. The base and the feet of the fairy do not fit perfectly together. This makes the fairy fall off the base sometimes before she takes flight. Also, it clearly states in the instructions to keep your hair tied back while using the fairy, make sure you heed that warning. Her wings could easy get tangled in hair when she is flying, and that would not end well for someone's hair. Also, if her battery is not completely charged, she will not function properly. She will fly into walls, people, etc. My daughter is able to easily manipulate the fairy, but I do not think it would be suitable for a child much under 6. Overall, the idea of this toy is awesome, I just think some things could have been done better in order to ensure higher standards of safety. Thanks to BzzAgent, I was able to try this product for free.

product_title: Powerful Amphibious Remote Control Car, Drives on Land & Water, 200 Ft. Control Range, 360 Degree Spins, LED Headlights
review_headline: Great product for a 7 y/o. Great customer service.  100% satisfied.
review_body: Pro's: 1)  RC car is great for my 7 y/o.  Bought it for his birthday.  Its quick, fun, and tears through most anything he hits.  Drives very fast on the driveway and road.  Hits the unmowed lawn with speed and maintains it throughout.  Up and down ditches like a champ.  Through mulched beds with ease.  He drives it through the forest in the back yard over hills and dirt bike ramps with ease too. 2) For a 7 y/o it took a few runs to get used to the skid steer, but that was expected. 3) OUTSTANDING customer service.  His left wheels started to 'stick' causing the car to not drive straight when commanded.  This happened w/in 3 months of purchase.  Emailed Kidzlane, and they took care of it with ease!  Very impressed with their desire to maintain good customer relations!  Thanks Kidzlane!  Cons: 1) Easy to flip.  If he drives to hard into a steep hill, or hits reverse on both wheels when going full speed forward, the vehicle will flip.  No biggie, but it scratches the roof. 2) Battery installation is difficult, requiring a screwdriver (provided).  Understand it's needed to keep watertight battery compartment, but I would think a quick latch system would work. 3) Battery life can be less than desired.  Quick solution was to purchase additional batteries for hours of fun.  Overall - this car is a beast for it's price, and my boy is loving every minute of it.  Kidzlane has been outstanding in their service.  Highly recommend purchasing this if you are considering an inexpensive RC car for your child.  Update, Dec 2015. I can't praise the Customer service of Kidzlane enough!  Our toy broke again, a plastic gear in the wheels stripped.  Kidzlane replaced for free!  If you like amazing Customer service - Go with these guys!

product_title: Fisher-Price Imaginext Alpha Star
review_body:
Ok so this is plastic spaceship for a toddler. I am not looking for German quality engineering here but this product is ridiculous. The factory / designer made no effort whatsoever to calibrate their design so it actually works.

Issues :
1, The space helmet has no way staying on the astronaut, the sizing is so off the sits on his head like he just grabbed the closes planter near by and called it a helmet. Trying to place the astronaut in the spaceship with the helmet on is impossible. There is not enough clearance to close the cockpit. So the helmet is useless, it just constantly falls off causing frustration.

2, Ok issue number one can be explained by, oh son he does not need the helmet in the spaceship ok..... However, the pilot itself it to large for the cockpit. A person really has to finagle and shove the guy in there to fit and for the cockpit to close. Same goes for getting him in and out again This is BS since the fundamental point of the toy.

Dear toy maker, let me tell you the "User Story" for the product. Three year old using imagination play with spaceship and astronout having adventures. For this the astronout has to be able to get in and out of his spaceship and travel to other locations and rinse and repeat. What they should not be doing is getting frustrating with trying put together 3 pieces of outerly poorly designed garbage..

product_title: SmartLab Toys Smartphone Science
review_headline: Made Me Curious to Learn More
review_body:
I picked this up for my granddaughter because she’s very interested in math and science right now and I want, as much as possible, to encourage her interests, especially when they are educational. As excited as I was to get this for her, I was even more thrilled when I actually got to open the box and flip through the book. It isn’t very big (only 24 pages) but there’s a lot of information on those few pages! I was tempted to test the kit out on my own smartphone but I refrained, although it wasn’t easy, because the book did make me curious about some things.

My granddaughter was just as thrilled as I was and started looking through the book and picking which experiments she would do first. There wasn’t enough time during our visit for me to witness any of these experiments but what grandmother doesn’t love seeing her grandchild enthusiastic about learning? I love this item and would absolutely consider buying more from SmartLab. Highly recommended.

product_title: Blast Zone Magic Castle Inflatable Bouncer
review_headline: Awesome!! Little heavy, but worth the work!!
review_body: Our family consists for a 2 year and 1 year, primary users, and 14 year old who occasionally jumps in. Even my 10 year old niece enjoys jumping in it. It's a great backyard size. I was a little concerned at first because it does say not to use with an extension cord and our outdoor outlets are too far away from any flat spot for bouncing. We have used it with this heavy duty extension cord a number of times with no troubles. The castle is easy to set up and is ready to go within a few minutes of pulling it out of the carrying bag. We place a tarp or outdoor blanket under it to help keep it clean and protect from any missed sharp objects. Take down is a little more work and requires a little more time but I am able to do it in under 20 minutes. The hard part is that its heavy and takes a little time to roll up well so that it fits nice in the carrying bag. My kids will play in it for hours. Thrilled to be able to add this to our backyard toys.

product_title: Harvest Moon 12" Sheep Plushie
review_body:
As a huge fan of the Harvest Moon series, I have collected all of the pre-order plush and Premium plush toys that Natsume has put out. That said, I was very excited for the New Beginning Premium sheep. It makes a great addition to my collection, but I must admit I was a little disappointed...it is not quite as nice as the others from the premium series.

First, this plush is unstable. It has tiny feet with no wires or anything to keep it upright. It is extremely top-heavy and will fall over or forward unless you put something underneath it's belly for support.

Secondly, the fleece material is not as soft as I've seen on other toys. It's not quite as soft and cuddly as I'd hoped.

One more thing of note, the description states that this is the sheep from A New Beginning. This is definately based off of the sheep from the Lost Valley.

To wrap it up, I do like this plush, but I would only recommend it to collectors. It's not easy to display, and it is not really soft enough to cuddle in bed.

product_title: Disney Pixar Cars Quad 6-Volt Battery-Powered Ride-On LIGHTNING MCQUEEN
review_body:
The Lightning McQueen theme is nice and ultimately why we got this, but the quad is lacking in a few areas, which are able to be fixed if you're handy/motivated enough.

- Turn Radius: This was pretty poor, it couldn't make the turn from driveway to sidewalk for my son. To fix this you need to disconnect the steering column and remove the column/handlebars then trim the notches in the hole to allow more turning.
- Range: You can fit a second 6V 4.5ah battery under the seat quite easily. You can hook it up in parallel for added run time or just leave it there so you can swap batteries if you're out on a walk and he runs out of juice (might need to carry a screwdriver to remove the seat then)
- Rough Terrain: barely moves through a yard and constantly gets stuck when the single drive wheel lifts off the ground. To fix this I acquired a second motor from a craigslist quad and put it in, goes like a champ now!
-No reverse: This can also be modded in utilizing an SPDT switch.

Overall, not the best platform, but not the worst. Shortcomings can be fixed if you're okay modifying the toy. The size is very nice for the 1-3yo group, though the younger kids tend to have a little trouble with the finger "go" button. If you plan on using this in a yard and don't want to bother with converting it to 2WD yourself I recommend you stay away from this one and find a model that drives both rear wheels.

product_title: Nerf Rebelle Secrets & Spies Arrow Revolution Bow Blaster
review_body: Although I had some initial doubts as to build quality and durability, my daughter has had a blast with this toy bow.  It's listed as ages 8 and up (mostly for legal reasons, I'm sure), though kids younger than that will be able to handle it.  The unit may mimic a compound bow, but it isn't one, so the draw strength is quite low, and even the little ones will be able to draw it and fire an arrow.  The arrows are tipped with soft, collapsible rubber, so they are quite safe (they also whistle as they fly).  The limitations on string draw and arrow weight/tip means that these won't fly super high or far, but just right for little kids to play and practice their shooting.  I'm also happy to see a product aimed for girls that isn't a doll or some other stereotypical "girly" toy!

product_title: AMT STAR TREK GENERATIONS KLINGON BIRD OF PREY MODEL KIT MIB
review_body:
I've had this model kit on my wish list for several months. When I initially added it, it was around $75, and I would check back every few days to see if the price dropped. (For some reason, the newer AMT Round 2 model of this kit isn't available at all anywhere that I could find.) Last week, when I saw it was down to $24.99, I knew I couldn't pass that up. Package arrived mint-in-box, and, even though one corner was a little crumpled, everything inside was still wrapped and in new condition. I was extremely pleased with how well the pieces of this kit went together. With the other kits from 20+ years ago, I'd always had trouble with some pieces not fitting correctly due to age and/or warping. But I got lucky with this one. Everything fit and glued together just like it was supposed to. And, as usual, I went with my own color scheme. It looks great sitting on my shelf next to the battlecruiser from Star Trek VI.

UPDATE:
I purchased a second kit, and I decided to try a different color scheme. (Plus, I think I like the attack mode wing configuration better than the flight mode.) Although I'm still not sure I chose the right shade of green for the ship's hull, I definitely like the second color scheme better than the first.

product_title: Spin Master Games - Pop Stream Board Game
review_headline: When I Downloaded the App I had to Reboot My iPad, but this is Wholesome Entertainment for Youths
review_body:
There are a number of things that I like about this game, although it is intended for a much younger audience. Before talking about what I like, I will explain those points that I found either not good, or not so nice.

I searched all over for instructions but those that are provided with the merchandise, and those offered at the Amazon product page are minimal. I can understand that providing written instructions is a cost they want to avoid. But, remembering that this is targeted for kids, who are likely to seek or need parental help, written instructions would be preferred.

Still, since the app is an integral part of the game, possibly, having a video demo would be a good way to go. Only by scrolling through the rules and instructions was I able to learn that I must wage a bet on the letter desigbating my selection. Until I chanced upon the instructions at the opening screen, I was on the edge of quitting and writing a harsh review.

Why harsh? Because I had already been forced to reboot my Mini iPad, since it crashed three times while starting the app. The reboot took care of that, but then I was stumbling through the game unable to cast a choice (because I hadn't wagered anything and didn't know how to confirm my wager and choice.

Still, once I did get everything going, I found this to be a terrific game for kids, say, from 8 to 16 years of age. Mind you, it will not likely take the world by storm the way Trivial Pursuit did during the eighties, but it will be a game that many kids will enjoy.

I also can see how such a hybrid game/app could be used in other endeavors. Education is one. For instance, a kid could read a book that is linked to YouTube videos, then take a quiz that tests them on what they've learned.

Another feature I enjoyed was the selfie, modified for comic effect. I also like how the app can see the board positioning.

Overall, I found the game is suitable for youth whose parents are looking for fun, wholesome entertainment.

CAUTIONARY NOTE: There are board pieces that could pose a choking hazard for children under three years of age.parents are looking for fun, wholesome entertainment.

CAUTIONARY NOTE: There are board pieces that could pose a choking hazard for children under three years of age.

product_title: TOMY Inside Out Large Figure
review_headline: A lot of personality in this little doll
review_body:
Truly sad: “I’m sadness.” Yes, you truly are. After hearing what this tiny doll has to say, I was feeling pretty sad myself. It’s not just the all over blue. When sadness speaks, she kind of slumps to the side in an all around sad and pathetic.

“We shouldn’t go in there. That’s a bad idea. ”
“Find the fun. I don’t know how to do that.”
“I don’t think that will work.”
“I’m sad.”
“Goodbye friendship. Hello loneliness.”

The Inside Out dolls are much better than stuffed toys. These are toys that are about emotion. That makes them worth their weight in gold.

product_title: FirstBIKE Cross Bike with Brake
review_headline: Great!! solid and light bike.Top quality.
review_body:
Great bike, I didn't buy it in Amazon but from the manufacturer's website.
I'm glad I went with this model, I little more expensive but real pneumatic all terrain tires and a hand break.
I bought the lowering kit to help my kid feel safer with both feet flat in the ground.
Very solid bike yet very light, my 2.5 y.o. kid can pick it up and move it around.
It takes a couple of weeks for kids to get used to two tires, but once they find the balance point they progress very quickly. my kid went from not being able to stand and move the bike alone to race (me running behind) and in about 2 months.
My kid already knows how to use the brake and I'm sure the transition to a pedal bike will be smooth.

review_body: Kahuna is a two player game that requires strategy and a bit of luck. It was a big hit at my twelve year old's sleepover, with the kids picking up game play quickly. They rated it 5 stars and declared it loads of fun. When adults in our family played, they didn't find it nearly as compelling, rating it 3 stars. The fact that's its two player is a big plus and I like the fact that it appeals to a fairly wide range of ages. They all found the cards a bit flimsy but that was the only complaint as far as the actual game quality. Overall, I think it'll get played most often by the tweens while the adults find other games that are a bit more challenging.

product_title: ZOOB Z-Strux Scorpion Driller
review_body:
This set is a departure from the LEGO bricks, and with this set you are only building vehicles.

I felt like the directions (color booklet) were easy to follow for an adult or a teen, but for a younger kid it just is too challenging. However you don't have to be limited to the directions, you can make any sort of free form vehicle you want. It's nice though, to have the guide in case you need a little bit of guidance.

Pieces are sturdy and are not going to break on you. Most of the "joint" pieces are yellow with a few black and orange ones thrown in. Set comes with a set of wheels (tank style), one drill attachment, one construction type man with a hat, and a pod for the man to fit in so he can drive. There are enough pieces to make a very elaborate vehicle.

You can buy other sets and combine them together, and I suspect if your child is a fan of these that is what will have to happen. The box says ages 6 and up, but I'd say the ideal age would be 8 and up, because by that age they can read and follow the directions without adult help.

product_title: ALEX Toys Craft My First Sewing Kit
review_body:
I purchased this item for my 9 year old grand daughter for Christmas. At first she didn't seem interested so I didn't push it. After sitting on her shelf for a couple of months, she finally expressed an interest in learning to start to sew. Upon opening it and going thru everything we decided to get started on the basic pouch so she could get used to the simple steps.

The instructions were not clear enough for a nine year old to understand without lots of help from an adult. I would like to have seen "kid friendly " instructions included so she could feel more successful.

The thread was very hard to get through the eye of the needle that was included in this kit, so I gave her a needle with a larger eye, from my sewing kit.

After the beginning project, she was able to complete the stuffed animal projects with a little to no assistance from me.

Although I do not sew as a hobby, this was a good place for my grand daughter to start exploring the sewing world and I think shes hooked!

product_title: LeapFrog LeapFrog LeapPad Platinum Kids Learning Tablet
review_headline: My son loved his leap pad
review_body:
My son loved his leap pad.. but in the divorce some how my wife just took it n that was that - none at my house for him.

So in comes this version of it. already hes amazed. its better, bigger, nicer, sleaker. cooler, more features n functions for sure!! We like it has a much larger screen n better graphics (especially for kids!). Its rough n tough but id suggest get a case and a screen protector on amazon or ebay! Sound quality is superb for sure.. The stylus is a bit better than past versions too.. and the battery is a HUGE step up! omg... much much better for sure.

It says its 8gb but it seems like 4 or 5 is avail to use.. is the rest for pics or what?? i dunno but its weird. def gotta register online for sure.. The wifi is for buying n downloading apps only - but either way i still love this!

So, this device has loads of potential but if you are planning to give it to a kid who has played with an IPad or Kindle Fire, you might have a disappointed kid. They might even look at you like you have three heads and came from a different planet. Also, the age range listed it 3-9. Once again, no 6-9 year old that I know is going to be happy with the limited offerings of this device.
