product_title: Schleich Spinosaurus Toy Figure
review_headline: Looking forward to getting more Schleich pieces.
review_body: This is the first Schleich product I've ever had, so I looked up the spinosaurus, and found that experts no longer think it looks like the Jurassic Park type, but the back legs were shorter and the spine fin was not humped, but rather wavy, and it had webbed feet.  Probably, it was an aquatic creature that lived on fish. That being said, this is still an impressive monster that was the largest dinosaur ever, and the toy is impressive, too.  The detail is most impressive, with the scales, teeth and tongue.  The jaw opens and shuts, but my two year old doesn't mess with that.  He's been in the sand box, Play-doh, and tub so far and no chipping of the color or pieces yet.  I love that the feet are perfectly balanced.  You know how sometimes only two feet are on the ground and the others totter?  Not this one.  It has a good heft to it and even the tongue is raised.  The colors don't bleed into another area.  This is a high quality product.  My only question is, why did they say it was violet?

product_title: LHI 250mm Pro Pure Carbon Fiber Quadcopter Frame Kit + CC3D Flight Controller + MT2204 2300KV Motor + Simonk 12A ESC + 6030 CF Propeller Prop
review_headline: Great kit for my first build
review_body:
I'm really satisfied with this kit. This was my first build of anything RC, and although it wasn't the breeziest thing ive ever done, it was do-able without a lot of frustration. There are numerous youtube videos that explain how to assemble these kits if you aren't sure what you're doing, so id recommend those.

The kit includes most of what i needed, but I had to buy nylon hex spacers for mounting the flight controller after the kit came because I assumed there would be some included, but there were none. There were all the screws needed (and some extra) but no spacers. There is some piece of an adapter that comes in the kit that i can only assume is a battery connector, but I opted to buy some XT60 connectors because that seems like the new standard.

Once I got it all assembled, the kit is very very sturdy. It does not feel like its going to break easy, and after 6 days of flying and probably 20 crashes, it does not seem to have any structural issues. Ive cartwheeled it in tall grass plenty of times, and while the plastic props I bought can get bent easily, the frame holds up great. I did break a small piece of it off in the back by flying backwards into a house, but even so its still very sturdy. The carbon fiber blades that come with it are good quality, and they fly much steadier than the plastic gemfans i bought, but i was able to break one pretty easily nonetheless. They hold up great for crashes, but don't let them hit anything hard like concrete because they can break more easily.

One of the downsides of this kit that i didn't like is that the holes for the motor were not drilled out enough. I had to drill all of the motor holes out more myself. Not only was it too narrow for the screw to fit, the holes weren't tall or wide enough to accommodate the screw hole patterns on the motors. Be prepared to have to drill the motor mounts. And i was able to loose the dampening camera mount easily so i'd say don't fly with it on unlessyou are going to use it.

Everything in the picture comes in the kit, including the two wire pieces and the two heat shrink cables. I was a little concerned that it might not come with a power distribution board because it was not listed in the description so i bought another one anyways, but i can confirm that it comes with one inside the kit. All in all, this was a great buy and im really happy with it. I mean, you can't beat the price, this has the same stuff that kits that cost 50 dollars more have.

product_title: Tamiya 70168 Left/Right Independent 4 Speed Double Gearbox
review_body:
This is not really a 4-speed transmission, you cannot shift gears. What it is is a gearbox with 4 gear ratio options.
This kit is fairly easy to assemble, but beware, there are MANY SMALL PIECES. The instructions recommend using the included grease, but I found that the grease added SIGNIFICANT drag. I doubt that the gears will wear unless you plan on running it constantly for long periods of time. I chose to clean the grease off in favor of reduced drag. You will also need to clip the base plate for it to fit. (if you are using one)
I am using this for a bluetooth arduino robot.

Pros:
Easy directions

Cons:
The grease adds excessive drag

product_title: Schleich Riding Arena Play Set
review_body:
We're great fans of Schleich products - they are 'heirloom toys' quality meant to last several kids rather than the 'play and destroy' cheap toys so prevalent today. As well as hand details and care, expect a very nice product that you can that displays beautifully when not in use. So yes, very much worth the higher cost.

With the Riding Arena set, we have a nice introduction to the Schleich horse world. The set includes a beautiful hand-painted horse, saddle and accessories that can be outfitted, and a riding paddock area with fence. It may seem sparse at first but when paired with the playmat that is sold separately, it makes for quite a nice set piece. What we like about the arena is that it is open - so the horse can be easily seen when played with - the building doesn't get in the way. Opening windows make an additional nice touch.

We greatly enjoy our Schleich horses and sets and I enjoy having a toy that can be passed down to each child and then saved for grandchildren one day.

product_title: Mermaid's Quiet Moment 1000 pc Jigsaw Puzzle
review_body:
We had a great time completing this puzzle! The last puzzle we completed was back in the late 90's, so we were pretty rusty. I thought it was pretty challenging and we had to constantly reference the box illustration, especially for the kelp, mermaid tail, and mermaid hair. We spent about 45-50 total hours between the two of us to complete it. I think without looking at the box illustration, it would have taken us twice as long to complete! So many times we thought a piece must be missing, but then we would find it and laugh.

We separated out the edges first, and once we got the border complete, there were still several "edge looking" pieces left that ended up in the middle, which made it more challenging and I thought this was a nice touch. There were also a lot of very unique curvy pieces, which added to the fun. There were two instances where two pieces were still connected to each other as they hadn't completely been punched through, which was no big deal.

The overall quality is great! It really is a beautiful puzzle, as other reviewers have stated! The illustration is very vibrant and colorful. We plan to glue and then frame it! We look forward to our next SunsOut puzzle!

product_title: LeapFrog Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles Imagicard Learning Game and Bonus Booster Pack
review_body:
My boys ( now in their 30's) loved TMNT so I thought my 5 year old grandson might love them too. I was right. He was right on this game and enjoyed playing with it right away. He plays games on my Kindle all the time so he's got it down pat. They are so quick now. When I was five we had a huge "Fun With Dick and Jane" book on our desks. Sigh. I am aging myself. These kids are just so much more clever.

There are two things that I am not crazy about. The cartridges are now cards. Even though they come in a really great tin box that my grandson loves, it would be easy to lose them or bend them. My daughter-in-law is very good about these things but I worry about that. The other thing I don't care for is that you must complete a level to move one. This may be good for adult gamers, although I admit I get frustrated with that, but for kids it doesn't take long before they get bored and put it aside. There's just so many times he's going to try before he loses interest.

He is having a wonderful time and learning math so you can't beat that. I love the LeapFrog product and have never been disappointed with the quality.

product_title: MTG Magic the Gathering - Duel Decks: Zendikar vs. Eldrazi Sealed
review_body:
Bought this and have to say it rapidly is becoming one of my favorite duel decks. I chose Eldrazi - my hubs picked Zendikar. We are decent magic players and so far we are dead even for wins/losses on our picks.

Both decks need a good set of drops - and once that happens it's a steamroller situation. There feels to be a good balance between the two - tho I think Eldrazi is the stronger deck. Using spawn as land to cast is a great mechanic that churns out the creatures and helps with low-cost blockers.

Great cards. Fun mechanics. Really interesting to play. Winner in my book.

product_title: Wolfe Face Paint Kit, Professional Face Painting Palettes - Essentials (12 hydrocolors)
review_headline: For more than just face painting!
review_body: This is my first product like this, I bought after I did some research and weighed a few other options, and I'm glad I did. The price was right for the variety of colors you get. It is tricky to get the hang of, the amount of water needed for it is really very little, but it also depends on what method of application is used. Get this and have fun! It just takes a bit of experimenting to get the colors as opaque or sheer as you'd like and to blend colors. I have bright red hair and have used it with a small angled eyeliner brush to get beautifully bold orange and red eyebrows to match that last all day and night. I've also filled in tattoos for a fun pop of color and used it for super bright lips. It does come with two decent little brushes so that's a plus. I use either a beauty blender or cheap wedge sponges for bigger areas. Remember to thoroughly wash your brushes / sponges with SOAP and water because this stuff is very pigmented!

product_title: Tooth Chests (144/PKG)
review_headline: Defective product that will NOT stay closed
review_body:
I really wish I'd listened to all of the negative reviews. I'm a volunteer at a primary school clinic, and our kids are dropping baby teeth like crazy--at lunch, in their classrooms, and even in the hall right outside the clinic. We started out the school year (two weeks ago) with 30 tooth holders, and now we're down to about 5. Amazon.com to the rescue! Well, not quite....

I received my (well packaged, well padded) box containing the mini tooth chests within the 2-day Prime shipment estimate, which is good since we're in a bit of a pinch. The bag contained 3 colors of chests--purple, pink, and orange. It would have been nice to get additional colors (such as the ones in the photo), but at this point I'm not picky; we just need something that will safely store those bloody baby teeth so the kids can take them home and let the Tooth Fairy do the rest. Having read a few of the negative reviews, I realized that I needed to test the chests before I brought them to school. The first pink chest closed just fine. The next one was was missing a tab that secures the "lock"--it didn't stay closed. A third purple chest was missing a tab, so of course that one wouldn't stay closed. I tested 20 of these chests, and only 6 would stay closed. After some quick calculating I realized that out of 144 chests, there probably were only around 40 that would stay closed. Sorry for the language, but that is some p*$$-poor quality control, and I am not a happy customer.

I've started the return process stating that these chests were "defective"--hopefully I will get my $$ back so I can order tooth holders that will actually perform the job as described.

The screw just dropped out of the pendulum base, two of the medium axles were smaller in diameter than the rest, so some wobbling, and that whopping long pendulum stalk is of no use; the dowelling warps easily due to its length, and it just "sways" back & forth in a circular motion.... lacking stability.... would be better having a double-dowelled pendulum. review_headline: They are fine if you dont crash
review_body:
These are just plastic. If theres any sort of glass fiber in there, I cant see it. When you break a carbon fiber prop, you can see the layers of fiber criss crossed in there, but with these they have the same consistency the whole way through. They are fine if you dont crash, but they seem to hold up well enough even if you do. If they hit anything hard its basically guaranteed to break, but in my case i crash mostly in grass so they tend to last through a few crashes.

These are just OK for flying. If you've never used carbon fiber props and only used these then you are missing out because CF flies much smoother, but in a pinch these will do.

Mine didn't come with the spacers or adapters or whatever they are but that's ok i didn't need them anyways.

product_title: Green Toys Block Set
review_headline: Oddly shaped and not all pieces connect together
review_body:
Building blocks have been around for ages. Many companies have tried their hand at this classic toy and the fundamentals have remained the same: stacking blocks that connect/fit together. Then you have these. First of all, the blocks are oddly shaped. They're very rounded along the edges and they taper up so the bottoms are wider than the tops. The underside is simplistic when compared to a Lego product, being that there isn't a specific channel for each "bump" to connect into. When stacking like blocks (two bump to two bump, four bump to four bump, etc.) they connect alright enough. But don't try to "bridge" two pieces together with a smaller piece on top as it merely sits on top of the bottom blocks and does not press into place at all.

Also worth noting is that the color distribution varies from that in the stock photo. In the set I received the pitched pieces are blue, the 4 bump blocks are green, larger blocks are orange, and 2 bump blocks are yellow.

We've been really impressed with Green Toys and I had no reason to believe this product would be any exception. Sadly I was mistaken. The build of these is on par with Green Toys (thick, sturdy and smooth plastic) but they totally missed the mark on design. I would not purchase any more of these, especially given the high price point for 18 blocks. Sadly I cannot recommend these as they're more frustrating than anything else.

product_title: Pathfinder Adventure Card Game: Wrath of the Righteous Base Set
review_headline: Sword-and-Sorcery Adventure Ready to Play Any Time You Are!
review_body:
Wrath of the Righteous (WotR) is a table top game that uses a combination of cards and dice to create a high fantasy adventure for 1 - 4 players (more if you have the character expansion pack). The game is cooperative - all players work together to achieve each game scenario's goal. Everything you need to play is in this one box (dice, cards, rules), though expansions and various accessories are also available. The game itself is a hybrid of both traditional board games and roleplaying games (RPGs) - shuffled cards determine what treasure you will find and monsters you will face, and your character becomes stronger after every scenario as he/she battles the hordes of darkness. No game master (GM) is required, though a moderate amount of setup and takedown time is necessary for each scenario.

Wrath of the Righteous is relatively easy to learn to play, but will require some reading of the rulebook in order to properly understand. Each player controls a different character with special abilities and equipment (represented by cards). Characters take turns searching locations and dealing with what they discover - be it monsters, treasure, or horrible villains. Cards are played to represent what the character does or uses, and dice rolls determining success or failure.

In my opinion, the Pathfinder Adventure Card Game (ACG) is incredibly fun, and Wrath of the Righteous is one of the most enjoyable sets so far. WotR allows a high fantasy adventure experience whenever a player wants it, without the need for a willing GM or an exact group of friends to properly play. I still love traditional roleplaying games (along with their flexibility and potential for incredible story experiences), but this ACG is also a great deal of fun - I highly recommend it.

Rating: 4.5 out of 5 stars (rounded to 5). An incredible game for those looking for high fantasy adventure. Does require some setup and takedown time, as well as a decent understanding of the rulebook.

Tip: Do not mark the cards in this set. Either print a character sheet and mark it to track character progress, or purchase card sleeves and then mark on them with a felt-tip ink pen (the sleeve goes over the card, but can be removed when you want to play the character over). Sleeve size will most likely be Standard Card Game Sleeve size, though this can vary slightly by manufacturer.

Accessories and Expansions: WotR and the other PACGs have a number of accessories and expansions available for them - everything from new adventures (called "Wrath of the Righteous Adventure Deck" and the number) to miniatures that represent the characters and contain unique cards ("Pathfinder Iconic Heroes"). None of these things are necessary for new players to have, and may even create unnecessary confusion. For those people that really want to start with a more complete PACG experience, however, I would recommend two possible purchases: the Wrath of the Righteous Character Add-On Deck ($20 or less retail on release) and the Pathfinder Adventure Card Game Mat (retailing at roughly $25-$30 on release). The character add-on deck provides more characters for players to choose from; the play mat makes it easier to figure out where cards should be placed, and helps prevent them from sliding (not to mention making the game look more organized and appealing, IMO). These accessories/expansions are nice to have, but not necessary to enjoy the game (especially when first purchased).

product_title: Thames & Kosmos TK1 Telescope & Astronomy Kit Science Kit
review_body:
Even though I am not a child, I am lucky to have two granddaughters, 9 and 15 years old, to share this telescope with. I have very little experience with telescopes, although I am very familiar with other optical instruments (microscopes/optical test equipment). Where I am a complete newbie is in locating stars and planets - I'll be lucky to find the moon! - but I am beyond excited to learn and have signed up for a beginner's astronomy course. I have also downloaded an app called Star Walk 2 on my iPad, which will hopefully help me to identify what we see in the sky.
The telescope came in a huge package in perfect condition. It took me about 30 minutes to put it together, the directions were clear and I did not need any tools. Everything is sturdy, stable and very well made. The telescope was larger and more impressive looking than I had imagined it would be. Several lenses are included, and a nice booklet which clearly explains how to start.
I don't live in a place where it gets super dark at night, due to lights from a nearby city. However, we own a rural property where there is some open sky available, and this is where we will be having stargazing nights.
I live in the Tampa Bay area of Florida, and since it is our rainy season, it has rained and been cloudy every single evening for the past two months, and there is more rain on the way. We will have to wait until we have a clear night to find some extraterrestrial objects.
I am really happy to have this telescope, and I am impatiently waiting to venture outside with it.
As a gift for a child I think this would be fantastic! It is not at all toy-like, its quality is high, and I can't think of a better gift for a fledgling astronomer.

product_title: WLToys V911 V2 New Version 4 Channel 2.4G RC Helicopter RTF with 3 LiPo Batteries
review_body:
5 star fun, 4 star quality. I have flown these helicopters for several years with my son. I would say its the perfect step up from like the syma s107. The micro size is very durable for high speed crashes, however it makes the copter nearly unflyable outside in the wind.
The pluses: great for the price, parts are cheap (you can buy any part). Good power and a quality controller. Easy to fly - with practice, and I still crash a lot. Only the faster crashes will cause possible damage.
Negatives: When you receive this heli GLUE THE TAIL MOTOR MOUNT DOWN TO THE BOOM! If you crash tail first into the wall the mount will slide forward and shear the wires off (yes I did it before). I wish the quality of motor was better, the one you see I replaced both motors, it is the oldest heli I have however (I have 3). The amount of plastic in the rotor causes the flight characteristics to change and frequent trimming. The drive gear will be ruined quickly without killing the power before a crash.
Tips: Glue the tail motor mount down. Kill the power before a crash and don't let it flop around on the floor. I would say 6-7 years old to fly this without destroying it. I would order: main drive gears, balance bars and main blades. I have not broken the tail blades yet. There are great kits with everything besides the motors for around $10 including all the usual broken parts plus a new canopy and skids. The main drive gear I had to order individually. Don't overhead the motors too badly, they may begin to turn slowly and have to be replaced, warm not hot.
Have fun!

Prowl is loaded with articulation and comes with a tri-barreled rifle and the hand/foot piece for the giant Combinor. I wasn't looking to complete all 5, but I might now. Prowl alone puts all my cons from Bruticus to shame.

The detailing is alreay pretty nice, but I'm thinking of lining it with a black paint pen to bring out more of the detail.

The comic doesn't feature much of Prowl though. That seems to be a habit with Hasbro now. Oh well.

You see Prowl, get him. You won't be disappointed.

review_body: Fabulous puzzle. You need a strong light and/or a magnifying glass, but you do not need - and shouldn't use - the box! Everything goes together clearly, and there are lots of hints in the pieces itself, even if you can't remember whether Krakatoa is east of Java or west. (The movie said, east. The movie was wrong.) I know that from the picture it looks tough, with great expanses of brown. In reality, there are less than a couple of dozen pieces without some distinguishing feature that tells you at least the direction in which it faces.

product_title: ZMart Fun II Digital Chess Timer Black with Red LED
review_headline: Great Clock, but Scrabble lovers would want more Inputs.
review_body:
Clock is as advertised. Good build. Fine display. One issue I observed though is that the player touch button on my clock is so sensitive that at one point while playing it keeps activating itself to start the other guys timer without being touched. This happened severally during that game. Although after switching off and on I haven't noticed this again, I just hope it doesn't repeat itself as that would be a factory flaw.

Now on a second and personal note though, the reason I bought the clock was for Scrabble and not for Chess. The manufacturer did a great job in including the Scrabble mode of 25mins and negative countdown penalty at zero. However, some scrabble players don't play the full tournament 25mins game when playing casually or in clubs. Also, certain tourneys (not all) advise 20mins play to save time for the whole games.

This means that scrabble users want to be able to play a 15 or 20mins game with the negative countdown penalty feature as well when clock reaches zero. At present it's only the Scrabble mode that has that feature, and scrabble mode is compulsorily 25mins.

If the makers can add this feature, market for his product from the Scrabble community would soar as my fellow playmates are already loving the clock. It's not so common in the Scrabble circles. This is personal though as the clock addresses all areas it advertised quite well

Other than that, great clock. Nice to have. And more affordable than the high-end variants.

product_title: Bandai Hobby Star Wars 1/72 Tie Fighter Building Kit
review_body:
One of the most iconic vehicles in cinema history, I've always found the T.I.E. Fighter an inspired design. I never purchased any of the Fine Molds kits when they came out, (although I really wanted to). The detailing is as crisp as the very best Japanese aircraft kits I own. I haven't assembled it yet, but the fact that it's a snap-together kit, engineered to the highest quality is simply amazing. I saw a review on you tube for the 1/72 scale
X-Wing kit & the reviewer said that there was no need of glue, or filler! That's astounding! I expect the same is true for most, if not all of these offerings. It is smaller than I would like..(1/48 is my scale of choice for fighters), but a real gem nonetheless. My hope is that the sales warrant more 1/48 scale kits of the Star Wars fighters, however I'm very pleased with the results of Bandai Company's commitment to the Star Wars license. Well done!!

product_title: Hot Wheels 1995-415 Roll Patrol Street Eaters Series 4 of 4 1:64 Scale
review_headline: Very Nice Ape Like Bonnet (Hood) Image.  Windshield is a Bit Fragile Though
review_body:
What's not to love about the artwork on this thing? It's got an ape like face on the bonnet with a mouth with tongue and that little thing that hangs down the back of the throat, as well as very sharp teeth, the mouth also extends down both sides of the front of the vehicle. The car is a nice tan colour and also has black stripes which resemble hair on the back half of the sides. It has an orange spare tyre, front bumper, plastic interior and even the undercarriage is also orange. The undercarriage is made of metal too.

There's a few fragile parts of the car where plastic attachments meet the metal body. Such as the clear windshield, this is definitely something that can snap easily. The black roll bar in the back looks great but is also not something you'd want to carry the car around by. The wheels are also pretty cheap but this was part of the 1995 mass produced budget line and the hubcaps do sort of match the colour of the body of the car. It's a pretty cool Jeep like car, if you can find one for a couple of bucks online somewhere you should definitely get one.

product_title: Pokemon Plush Doll Vivid Umbreon Cute Toy Gift for Kids 33cm (13")
review_headline: Lovely Lunar Feline -- The BEST Umbreon Plushie!
review_body:
Although this is not an “official” Pokémon product, this Umbreon plush is no doubt the biggest, cutest, softest, and BEST Umbreon available! It “purr-fectly” depicts this beautiful lunar black cat, just as he looks in the Pokémon games, with vivid colours, and spot-on accurate details.

You will not find a single identifying tag on this plush (no hang tag or tush tag), as it is a custom pattern based directly on the awesome TakaraTomy small Umbreon ([[ASIN:B00A84G21E Takaratomy Pokemon N-47 Umbreon/Blacky Best Wishes 8" Plush Doll]]) plush pattern (I have attached photos to compare the two) – only expanded to two times the size! It is a perfect replica of the real Umbreon, accurately designed, and not one detail is missing.

This Umbreon is very lifelike, and large – approximately 13 inches tall! He sits up on his own, excellently balanced, without any need for extra support, so you can easily display him on a bed, shelf, desk, or anywhere you would like.

The materials used to make this plush are high-quality. Like other reviewers mentioned, this Umbreon special in that the material used to make his fur is actually jet-black instead of the more grayish-black-looking shades used on some of the other Umbreon plushies by TakaraTomy and Banpresto. The black "fur" is also very soft and velvety to the touch. The circular golden markings on his forehead and legs are precisely embroidered with shiny bright yellow thread, and his catlike red eyes with slit pupils (also masterfully embroidered onto the face), are piercing and intense, true to the real Umbreon. He has a short feline muzzle with a tiny triangular black nose, and a cute little grin (although these details are somewhat difficult to see at first, as they blend in with his jet-black fur). All over, his figure is perfect and accurate! He is stuffed to purr-fection, and although he is very lithe in shape, he is super-soft, squishy, and very cuddly. His rabbit-like ears are stuffed thickly, so they stand upright do not flop, and they have beautiful golden yellow ring patterns around them. The tail is the same, constructed and well-stuffed, just like the ears. His feline paws and feet are very beautifully detailed, with digits sewn in. His lovely detailed front paws are sewn together by thick threads, and I would not advise separating them, as it might result in damaging the plush.

Being an Eeveelution fanatic and cat lover, I adore Umbreon (as well has his Psychic-type sister, Espeon), and could not be more delighted with this incredible plush. He is one of my top favourites, and is always there for me to cuddle. He is perfect to snuggle with; hugging a soft plushie comforts me and helps me sleep, and this Umbreon has become one of my main cuddle buddies. I call him "Phantom". :)

I ordered this beautiful extra-large Umbreon plush from a very kind and honest seller on eBay. These extra-large Eeveelution plushies are made in and sold from China, so it will take some time to ship, but it is worth the wait. Again, this is not an official Nintendo plush, but in my personal opinion it is actually better and more fairly priced than any official Umbreon plush currently available. I have both the small TakaraTomy Umbreon and the Banpresto “I Love Eevee” large Umbreon, but this Umbreon is my favourite because it is so large and soft. It is a truly awesome size, durable, well-made, and so cute! product_title: VTech Switch & Go Dinos Turbo Spur The Stegosaurus
review_headline: Fun transforming rev car with quiet sound effects
review_body:
This is a really cool dinosaur. It transforms into a car, but it still looks boxy like a dinosaur. There are only four flaps in the transformation, but it's pretty cool in its simplicity.

There is a battery that does sound effects, and the sound effects are actually pretty cool. There is a switch where you can turn the effects off, 1/3rd level sound, or full sound. It comes with a AAA battery included, and it starts out on the reduced sound setting. So, that way your kid doesn't get used to loud sounds coming from this right from the box. At first, I thought that the sound was broken, because it's so slight, but this is pretty awesome that you get to choose different levels.

There are two red sound buttons that you can press for different sound effects, and it makes different effects based on whether it's a dinosaur or if it's a car. So, overall there are about twenty different sound effects, which is a ton for a toy like this.

This is one of those cars that you can push a few times, and the wheels will keep spinning. Then you drop it on the floor, and it goes. At first, I thought that the battery would help propel it, but the battery is just for sound effects. There's a rev engine inside that you have to charge by pushing it on the ground a few times before you release it.

product_title: Andoer DIY Multirotor Flight Controller Set Open Source APM2.6 2.6 & 6M GPS & 433mHz 3DR Radio Telemetry & OSD & Power Moudel for RC Ground Station Hobby
review_headline: APM 2.6 is awesome for the price
review_body:
I have several authentic 3DR flight controllers and mostly use Pixhawk. I've got to say that this APM 2.6 is awesome. The firmware upload had no issue. Once I selected the correct baud rate, Mission Planner connected for telemetry and settings. Then I calibrated all the settings and was up in the sky. My initial testing had no issues, no crashes - way points and RTL worked as they should. For the price (sorry 3DR guys) this is the best I've seen.

I ordered from Andoer the first time. That's what this review reflects. I've ordered a second APM (same one) but this time it's showing it's sold by Kokorest. I hope the quality is same or better.

product_title: Ares AZSC305C Gamma 305C 3C/3S 11.1V LiPo Battery Charger
review_body: This item does not include a "LiPo Battery & Charger" as indicated in the item title. I hardly expected it to given the price, but sometimes you get lucky. The package only includes the charger (pictured),  and that does not even work for me. I used the 12v cable from my Turningy Accucell6 battery charger because the socket size is the same, and the red led came on. But when i plugged the battery in, all it would do is momentarily flash the green light and the red light stayed on, indicating it was doing nothing. According to the only included directions, which are on the front of the charger, when you plug in the charger to power the red light will come on. When you plug the battery in the green light is supposed to come on also. When I plugin a battery nothing happens except that momentary flash of green. It does not appear to be charging. I tried this with a 3S 2200 mah 11.1v battery that was depleted to 10v and an identical battery that was charged to about 90% at 12.3v and both did the same thing. There's no buttons on here so its anyone's guess to what its doing. And since the green light does not even stay on, I dont trust this thing.

review_headline: Great Sleeves, but not for Double-Sleeving

The sleeves hold up well, have a nice shuffle feel, and the artwork is great. I use these sleeves for when I draft, and they have no damaged corners from a month of FNM drafts.
That said, i bought these with the intention of double-sleeving my deck and they are impossible to double-sleeve with because of the size they cut the sleeves at. You would have better luck with the Glossy-finish Legion sleeves if you want to Perfect-Fit your expensive deck and have it look good. I just wish that Legion would make their Double-Matte graphic sleeves Double-sleevable.

product_title: Power Bank,URPOWER 12000mAh Portable Charger External Battery Pack Backup Charger for iPad Air iPad mini,iPhone 6 Plus iPhone 6s, 6 5s 5c 5 4s 4,Samsung Galaxy S5 S4, S3, S2, Samsung Galaxy Note Edge,Note 4 3 2, HTC One, Evo,Droid Dna, Motorola Atrix, Droid, Google Glass, Nexus 4 and Other USB-charged Devices(Apple Lightning Adapter NOT included)
review_body:
I spend a lot of time hiking and camping in remote locations and love having the Urpower Power Bank with me so I can keep my phone charged in case of emergencies and when I'm taking pictures. I received the 3000mAh External Battery Pack along with a USB cable that charges the Power Bank and can be reversed to charge my Samsung S5. I have included pictures for reference.

The power bank uses a Li-ion polymer cell battery that quickly and efficiently charges my device without overheating itself or my phone. It's compact size makes it easily portable and fits in my hiking pack without taking up much space and adding weight. The external battery has microchips that prevent overcharging, overvoltage and short circuits, so I have extra security when using it. Disclaimer: I received this product at no cost in exchange for my honest, unbiased review. Regardless, I'm very happy with the Urpower Power Bank and would happily purchase.

product_title: Loopdedoo Spinning Loom Kit Friendship Bracelet Maker
review_body: I was surprised at how easy it was for my daughter (age 6) to use this spinning bracelet loom with minimal assistance.  She absolutely loves being able to make bracelets for herself and her friends.  She finds this a bit easier than the "rubber band" bracelets that have been popular in recent years (and we usually have to help her quite a bit with those).  For me, the string style friendship bracelets have nostalgia for me from when I was a kid and used to make these.  I like how you have 6 different options with this kit for styles of bracelet.  Once you consider that you can use a variety of different colors, the possibilities of bracelets really are endless.  This would make a really great gift for crafty kids possibly in the 6-12 year old range.  It's a great crafting project and while the loom is plastic, it seems sturdy enough to hold up over time.  Replacement string is cheap and easily found at craft stores.  Overall, I'm very impressed with this product and may purchase others to give to her friends as birthday gifts.

product_title: 8pcs/Lot STAR WARS Clone Wars Soldiers Troopers Darth Vader C-3PO Darth Maul Minifigures Figures Model Building Blocks Bricks Learning Educational Toys Gift for Children KidsColorful
review_headline: Legos by another name, still the same.
review_body: Wow.  This was kinda amazing.  These are the same as legos.  My son really wanted a Darth Maul so I bought this set, which was half the price of a Lego Darth Maul figure, and he is thrilled.  Takes a bit more work because you do have to pretty much assemble each figure from scratch.  So you can buy these eight figures for under $7 or you can buy a fully assembled single Lego figure for about $15 to $20 (one of the Darth Mauls is $30).  So, it depends on whether you have more time or money.  Took me about 10 minutes to put them all together.  But, you don't get a box, which was someone's complaint that gave this a one-star review.  Yeah.  Right.  A box.  That I'm going to throw away.  Oh, and a hint.  3-CPO comes with a light saber for some reason.  If you look at Darth Maul's light saber handle, there's a spot on both ends for a saber beam.  Take CPOs beam and stick it in Darth Maul's handle and, tada, the infamous double-bladed light saber!  CPO never had a light saber anyway.  Jeez.

product_title: Diamond Select Aliens Minimates Series 2 Set of 4 2packs
review_body: Every1 of the 1st 4 Aliens films had ensemble casts.  A corollary of that is that the cast is very diverse.  There are men, women, and children; whites, Blacks, and a Hispanic; adults & a child; and, of course, an alien that goes through stages like a butterfly.  (Remember Brad Dourif's statement in "Alien Resurrection.")  You could play Ripley and Hicks as a romantic couple.  Add Newt to the mix and you can consider them a hodgepodge nuclear family.  If adventurous, you can pretend that Vasquez and Ripley got together in a Lindsey-Samantha thang.  I have 1 problem here.  Many toylines uses models of the same size.  I guess it reduces price.  You do want the toys so that small children in their oral phase won't swallow them.  However, Newt was a child much smaller than Ripley and the Marines.  Here she is presented as just as big.  You would think she was the cowardly female in the 1st "Alien" if you didn't read who the characters were supposed to be.  This whole collection is a type of camp.  Hardcore fans like Comic Book Guy from "The Simpsons" wouldn't open the box.  However, this ensemble may be nice as a campy item to have in your cube or on your desk at work.  I could imagine children loving the toys but having nightmares about the film, so be careful in showing it to them.

product_title: Leray Self Balancing Scooter Balance Motion 6.5" Two Wheel Hoverboard with Certified Safe Battery Pack (Black)
review_headline: One of the most fun and unique toys I've used in a long time
review_body:
I honestly can't stop using this, even just going back and forth around the hallways in my house is so much fun.

Yes, it looks a lot like a Segwey without handles, and that's pretty much exactly what it is. But it's even harder to get used to at first, because it feels so unnatural to lean forward or backward on something with only two wheels, and you don't even have handles as a safety blanket. But you really don't need them. You just have to learn to trust the device and ignore your brain's nagging about how it's going to make you fall over.

There is absolutely no assembly, so setting it up consists only of charging the batter, which is included, internal, and non-replaceable. This takes about an hour. But on a full charge, it has a decent amount of life in it. Between zooming around my house, and around my neighborhood sidewalks for over an hour, it was still going strong.

It also includes LEDs on the front of each foot, which are kind of nice although not really necessary. They help light your way a little bit, but if it was too dark to see without them, I'd still probably recommend against using it in the first place.

Although the LEDs kind of suggest which way is front and back, you can actually face either direction and the device will operate identically either way.

Actual usage is as simple as: angle each foot forward or backward depending on how fast you want to go. So if you lean both feet forward, you'll start going forward. If you have your right foot going backward, and left foot forward, you'll rotate clockwise. It is capable of going much faster than I even dare going, so while I couldn't get myself to max out its speed, I can definitely attest to it being very fast for what it is.

The trickiest thing about using it is going over bumps or cracks. Due to how it works, and how small the wheels are, even small bumps and cracks can be very disruptive. If any part of it leaves the ground for any period of time, it has a harder time detecting how much pressure each foot is pressing on it, making it unpredictable. So I would strongly advise using it in as flat and smooth of area as possible.

So basically, once you get past the initial learning phase, this becomes extremely fun as long as you keep it in a tame area without too many obstructions. I literally just hop on and off of it randomly throughout the day to zip around my kitchen and halls just for fun. Very addictive and unique way to travel!

*Pros*
[+] Works fantastically, self-balancing is spot-on
[+] Comes completely assembled so it is super easy to set up
[+] Batter life is much better than I anticipated
[+] It's surprisingly silent, even while traveling at high speeds
[+] Gets a lot of attention from onlookers simply due to its uniqueness and awesomeness
[+] Can go very fast! It's actually kind of scary when using it at high speeds
[+] Great style and design, looks sleek and holds up fairly well to general use
[+] Wheel LEDs are a nice touch to give you extra lighting towards the direction you're going
[+] FUN!

*Cons*
[-] Questionable handling of bumps, cracks, and obstructions... cruise carefully!
[-] Battery isn't replaceable, so if you don't use best practices to keep it conditioned, the whole unit becomes useless
[-] Pricey!r any period of time, it has a harder time detecting how much pressure each foot is pressing on it, making it unpredictable. So I would strongly advise using it in as flat and smooth of area as possible.

product_title: Lost Cities - The Board Game
review_headline: Simple, fun and approachable game for friends and family
review_body:
Bottom line: A great family board game that is easy and fast to play

Lost Cities - The Board Game on the surface is pretty easy to understand and play. If you can count to ten in order, you pretty much have all the skill required to play. That makes the game pretty open to all ages, although 9 or 10 would probably be the younger limit to be able to enjoy playing the game. Playing a card moves one of your pieces across the board, and every spot on the board has a point value.

There are two basic versions on how to play, the short game and the long game. Short games are basically one round and take a bit more than 20 minutes, and the long games basically are three rounds of the game and take a bit more than an hour. There are other variations you can add on top of that, and with all board games you can always make your own house rules. For us, we enjoyed playing it where the tiles on the game board were not flipped over until a player’s piece landed on that spot—we felt that added to the exploration theme of the game and made it more fun for us, but that’s just one example.

Game board, card and pieces are all high quality and well made. They should last a very long time with normal gameplay.

While simple, we found the game fun and very approachable. It’s easily a top choice for a casual game night with friends and family.

Although the game says it is for 14+, I got this to play with my 10 and 7yo-both of whom enjoyed it quite a bit!  By the 3rd round, my 7yo was beginning to get some of the techniques involved to keep her piece safer from the magnetism of the other pieces.  A game lasts at most 5-10 minutes... so, it's a quick game for short attention spans as well.

product_title: WowWee Robotic Enhanced Vehicles (R.E.V)
review_body:
This is a great toy that just pulls you in and suddenly hours have passed.

First impression is that these little cars are sturdy. They have a nice heavy solid feel even without batteries. Oh - you'll need 8 AA batteries because the cars do not come with batteries. The battery trays are held in place with a small bolt and the bolt threads into something metal - way less danger of stripping those threads. Nice.

I ended up using an old ipad (2ish years old) to run the r.e.v. app because my android tablets (3 or more years old) weren't compatible. Minor annoyance - the google play store didn't tell me if any of my other android devices were compatible. Also, the key to finding the app seemed to be searching for "r.e.v." including the periods. The app installed normally onto the ipad. Also - something I really liked is that the android version said the app doesn't require extra permissions. I didn't notice permission stuff on the ipad. Still, this is great because it means that the app isn't helping itself to your contact list n' stuff.

Upon linking to the first car, the ipad said the car's firmware needed to update. The first update attempt hung. The FAQs on the instruction booklet said to turn the car off then on. That worked. The second car required the exact same procedure including the hang. Still, they did update quickly.

The app is intuitive. Touch the screen, move your finger, see what happens, adapt until you get it right. At first, the car seemed twitchy and hard to control. Actually, it is touchy and hard to control. It doesn't take much to make that thing zip across the floor and ram a wall. Luckily, the car so very sturdy and held up to many rammings. But... you can run into stuff for only so long before you want to check out battle mode and the AI.

As before, the app is intuitive when it comes to setting up the car and the AI. The car has 4 "slots" for stuff like weapons, healing, shielding, etc. Messing around with the "AI" screen lets you pick which AI will suddenly grab control of the other car, ram your car, and shoot it up. There's a progression of tougher AIs to fight.

Next, tell the app it is time to fight, it counts down to zero (visually, not audibly) and then the AI springs to life, rams your car, makes shooting noises, and then the app says you lost the fight. The car battles do involve quite a few wrecks and rams. Again - these cars are sturdy for a reason. Sadly, the app, at least the 8/29/2015 version of it, doesn't tell you when you've won and there is no obvious way to restart. I could tell I'd won when the AI's health dial went to zero and the AI car wouldn't move anymore. I restarted by going into the AI screen and selecting a different AI which triggered a restart.

Oh yes - I ran the cars over carpet and tile. The carpet isn't all thick and luscious. There were no issues with running on either carpet or tile but the cars are fast on tile and make tighter turns on carpet.

The time really flies while fighting those AIs and that annoying twitchy handling is transformed into welcome responsiveness after a while.

I have yet to battle a human. That will change soon.

product_title: Blade Inductrix BNF Ultra Micro Drone with Safe Technology
review_headline: Perfect Noob Nano size Quad Rotor, stable, responsive, and inexpensive fun!
review_body:
OK. Did NOT purchase on Amazon as I think it's important to try and keep our local hobby shops alive and they can also be sources of help. Purchasing the Inductrix was the result of such help.

Been into RC stuff for decades but exclusively cars and trucks. Came across a link to a tiny little Estes Proto X and thought "well thats kinda cool" and ran out and bought the little bugger after watching some youtube videos which made it look super easy to fly... Same with the Blade Nano QX 3D which I also purchased based on the reviews and videos on youtube which went ON AND ON about how easy they are to fly... DON'T BELIEVE IT! Easy is all relative...

SO, I get home all excited, charge up my new little Quads ready to launch into a new Hobby filled with precision flying and cat chasing. However, this is was not the case. Instead I spent a good portion of my day trying to put tiny little rotors back onto the Estes Proto X and pushing motors back onto the motor mounts of the 3D... Some decent level flight was had, but not much, mostly I just spent my time putting them back together. It reminded me of a similarly doomed venture a few years ago with RC Helicopters, which ended with me giving away radios, batteries, chargers, and yes Helicopters. Turns out Skill with driving, riding, and video games does NOT translate into rotary wing aircraft.

ALL OF WHICH BRINGS ME TO THE INDUCTRIX. I was hesitant to buy the Inductrix, after all I had two frustrating quads at home already with STEEP learning curves, wasn't interested in adding more frustration. Felt as though my MAN CARD was already in jeopardy. However, as the radio to the QX 3D will bind with the Inductrix I took the Clerks advice at HobbyTown and purchased one.

WOOHOO! Success, finally a Quad rotor that doesn't shatter or shed rotors at every misstep, a quad that seems to WANT to fly and work with me to improve or actually develop quad skills. The Inductrix is STABLE, and perfect for someone who is a complete noob. It's quiet by comparison to the others and a great way to tiptoe into the whole drone/Quad thing. Decent run time, inexpensive batteries, and a truly solid performer. It's allowed me to establish true 5-8 minute flight times without terrorizing the cats, or shredding parts, very cool.

So, if you are New to RC flight do not hesitate, this thing is excellent, it's stable fun and follows directions better than the Estes Proto X, and Blade Nano QX 3D. However if you are NOT new then I might hesitate and all of this quads stability and lack of "tricks" might make it kind of boring for you.is STABLE, and perfect for someone who is a complete noob. product_title: Animal Planet Grow Eggs- Dinosaur - Hatch and Grow Three Different Super-Sized Dinos (Series 1)
review_body:
My kids were cheering when they Animal Planet Dinosaur Eggs arrived! They tore into the package and asked me what the eggs were. I explained we were going to place them in water and watch them hatch. We placed the eggs in a cup of water and a little over 24 hours later they hatched! The children were so excited to get to see the dinosaurs. They went to get them out of the glasses and did not want to touch them after that. I was curious so I picked one of them up. They felt really slimy! My children are special needs and have sensory issues. The slimy feeling is a sensory trigger for them. After about another 24 hours the dinosaurs dried out. Once they were dry the slimy texture disappeared. Once the dinos were dry the kids were happy to play with them. We got to use the cards included in the box to discuss each of the dinosaurs.

The one star I removed had to do with the weird texture of the dinosaurs when they were wet.

Disclaimer: I received this product at a discount in order to test the product and give my honest feedback.

The plastic that it is made from is surprisingly tough and has taken a good deal of abuse. I usually make my kids take their shoes off to climb in but it would probably be ok with them on too.  I'm sure it could be punctured but so far we have not had any issues. I also like that the seams were double-reinforced in the critical parts (the openings where they climb in and out). Older kids might be too rough for it but for mine (ages 5 and 3) it has been perfect. If you are thinking of buying this make sure you have a compressor or inflator handy!

product_title: Dr Kopter Mini 3.5 Channel RC Helicopter with Gyro, Blue
review_headline: Entertaining & does a lot for its size.
review_body: This is a very cute product.  It is very small, fits in the palm of my hand.  The concept is very clever in that it uses a dual rotor, self-stabilizing propulsion system.  It charges very quickly from the control box, which also doubles as a carrying case for the Kopter.  Apparently, I am not a natural born pilot and getting the hang of the controls has been challenging for me, but it has been immense fun learning "how to fly".  I would recommend this as a nice intermediate step towards flying the big remote control units which, of course, are several hundred dollars.  The price for this is certainly right, you get a lot for what you pay.

product_title: Venom 50C 3S 5000mAh 11.1v Water Cooled Marine 3 Cell LiPO Battery x2 Packs
review_body: For the money these batteries don't deliver what they promise . They require a large amount of water flow to work properly especially if you are using two or more at a time, you will need a dedicated water inlet to work properly . I feel the discharge rate has been greatly exaggerated , I have 35C venom batteries about 6 months old that out perform these by at least 25 % although they warm up a little under the same conditions . I think a trade off was made here with different labels and a 100% markup . i have had trouble with the quality off materials used on the electrical  connectors and corrosion under light use . These 50C batteries will stay cool but they take up more room and require a water redo, I do not recommend these batteries to anyone unless heat is a paramount concern , i would have been much better off investing in more research and less brand loyalty . I have been told that ZIPPY BRAND BATTERIES may be a much better alternative for price and performance . WHENEVER  POSSIBLE read the reviews AND shop different brands, unfortunately a newer product or limited selection may narrow your choices which asks the question why are more manufacturer's NOT making this -COST ?, CONSUMER NEED ? GIMICK ? . GOOD LUCK ! .

product_title: Little Tikes Easy Score Soccer, Hockey, Lacrosse Set with Net
review_body:
This set is poorly designed junk. The hockey puck does not slide on ordinary paved surfaces, nor would it work on grass. Useless. The soccer ball is pathetic. Its basically a dog toy sold in a set for kids. You can get a much better soccer ball for children at any sports store. As for the sticks and net, what you are getting is basically HALF of what you need to have any real fun. You get one net, and two sticks. But there are four attachments for those sticks: two hockey and two lacrosse. The attachments go on by way of a crude lock-in system that requires pushing very gently on a button-- to make the attachments go on-- but that requires a very HARD push to get them off again. My son and I could not get the lacrosse attachments off the sticks except by squeezing HARD on that button. Unfortunately, one of the buttons was squeezed so hard that it went in-- and did not pop back out again. Now that stick is junk. We have just one stick now and its staying on its lacrosse setting. You'll need to buy extra sticks if you want to enjoy this set with less stress, so that your hockey and lacrosse sticks are ready when your kids are and don't need to be changed. But I wouldn't even bother buying this set for its sticks because they are made from clunky metal-- why not just get your kids the right sized, lower-end equipment made from wood or plastic and that requires no assembly? The set makes enjoying sports horribly complicated.

The net went together easily enough, but its not something I'd want to take apart and do over again each time they wanted to play. So it takes up a large part of our basement. What I dislike most about the set is the cheapness of the materials. It has great gift appeal: It was my preschooler's favorite birthday present and his 7-year-old brother was even excited when it was opened. The picture on the box had my kids giddy to take it out right away. But once we had it out, and realized how little there really was to play with, the qualityof which was all around inferior, our excitement waned and this toy will probably make an appearance in next year's yard sale. Its a flashy toy with excellent gift appeal: Its best use is pretend-play for little kids. But keep in mind it has all the caveats of a self-assembled toy.

review_body: This is one of the best Green Toys we have.  We kept it outside ALL Summer and not one bit of fading, breakage or anything.  My son now has it indoors to play with in the bathtub.  The cars have been put through all kinds or testing with a toddler and they don't have any knicks or scratches to speak of or see. The boat is big and can be taken apart easily for washing (if need be.)  I have most of the Green Toys and have yet to be disappointed by any of them.  My son likes to put all of his toys on this little ferry and it holds a nice load.  The cars are the perfect size for toddler hands and are much bigger than a Matchbox sized car.  I highly recommend this over all of the Green Toys if you are getting your "first."  This is a prime example of how well they are made overall and what you will be getting if you decide to buy more.  My son uses his imagination with these toys more than any others out there.  Forget the toys that make noise, these will be played with much much longer.

product_title: D&D Next: Cleric Spell Deck 73902
review_body:
Standard size cards with a light laminate that should hold up forever since you never need to shuffle them. Much simpler than digging through the PHB over and over, but spell pages for the longer descriptions. Spell descriptions indicate all the relative information about casting time, range, requirements, and even concentration (with version 2).

We take the ready spells and arrange them by level, then place glass beads that represent the amount of spell slots we have next to them, different colors for each levels. As we cast a spell, we move a bead, and after a long rest we replace them. Saves a lot of erasing, and we've all canged to this card/bead system. If you can afford all the niceties, this is definitely worth the small cost.

product_title: Hasbro Games Twister Moves Hip Hop Spots
review_headline: Good coordination is required but it's all in good fun
review_body:
I have always been a fan of the original Twister game since I was a child so I was excited to receive this new updated version with a twist! My daughter, her friends and I had a ball playing this at her recent birthday party but only 2 people can play at a time so that was a bummer. The game is simple. You basically keep up with the beat by stepping on the colorful spots when lit up by the lights. Good coordination is required but it's all in good fun!

In order to keep up with your score digitally, you will need to purchase the Twister Moves Tracker separately. This is a great game that will get and keep you moving!

product_title: SunPrint Paper Kit
review_body: I stumbled across this by accident, and although it seemed a bit pricey for only being able to make 10 images, I thought this would be a fun project for my grand-daughter (age 9) to work on over the summer. I guess these kits have been around for a long time, but somehow I never knew about them...I think they are a great idea, and I had fun, too! Easy directions are on the back of the package. The kit is simple: inside of the package is the paper in a protective dark pack--don't let light hit the paper when taking out one sheet! and a thick piece of acrylic to hold the objects to be printed flat--there is an adhesive sheet protecting it that needs to be discarded first. We simply laid a large, flat piece of cardboard on the lawn in a spot where there was full sun. For the first picture, she made a simple design from pieces of torn paper to make a floral pattern...she put the print paper on the cardboard, arranged her design on top, and covered it with the acrylic. It took about two minutes for the light blue paper to turn white and then she just popped it into a dishpan full of clean water--I know now that it is best to change the water after every one or two pictures--and it slowly turned a dark blue, and ta-daa! There was the image! Pretty! From there, she tried 3-D objects (without the acrylic sheet, of course) and the one that turned out the best was a branch with fruit--the detail and depth came out great! I didn't see any refills available for the same size paper (about 8 x 10) but I was able to order a couple of 5 x 7 packs, so lots of opportunity to make more Sun Prints! I think this is a great kit for elementary school age kids (and I'm sure older kids could come up with some pretty creative uses, too) but for more than one child, with only 10 sheets, I think it would be best to have a refill on hand. In fact, if kids want to make Sun Prints with 3-D objects, the kit isn't needed at all, just save some money & purchase the paper by itself!

product_title: Let's Go Play Go-bowen 1000w / 48v/ up to 20mph/ 3-speed/ Battery/ Red Go-kart
review_body: I purchased the go-cart as a Christmas present. The only thing that required assembly was the rollover bar. You have to install the battery, and drop in and secure the steering wheel…that’s it. It took more time to remove the metal shipping frame than the assembly would have taken. I ended up returning it without assembling or charging it.  It was missing the pin to secure the steering wheel, the gear knob, and some screws for the rollover bar. The holes on the rollover bars were misaligned; so they could not be assembled. It required 2 different keys; I received 2 of the same key.. I received 3 batteries with no explanation for receiving 3.  The manual said there should be an accessory/tool bag, but there was not. Other than that the manual was useless.  It was a bad photo copy, very poorly written and did not match the go-cart I had.  I contacted the supplier about all the issues and the fact that the go-cart couldn’t be returned because of specialty shipping. They forwarded my email to the manufacturer. The Manufacturer shipped the missing parts overnight. However, they did not understand the misaligned screws on the rollover bars; therefore they were not replaced. I emailed photos of the misaligned holes on the rollover bars. While waiting their reply I decided to look up the Co. on the BBB web site.  There was one resolved complaint involving a request to return a go-cart for a serious safety issue.  That information, along with the issues I was having, lead me to the decision to return the product.  Long story short, after really pushing the return issue the Co., thankfully, allowed me to return the go art at their expense, for a full refund. I reassembled the shipping metal frame around the go-cart, secured it to the frame and wooden pallet with the wires it came with. I bought long thick plumbing tie wraps to tie down the box. I say all this to encourage you to keep all the packing material just in case.  I was delivered and picked up on an 18 wheelertransfer truck.

product_title: Step2  Naturally Playful Sand Table
review_body: I bought this to use as a water table for my son, he is 2, and he LOVES it.  I didn't want the ones that are actually sold as a water table because they have so much extra stuff along the sides of the table there is no room to play with the water.  This is the perfect height for my son to play with.  At first I thought it was not going to be deep enough for water play but when I filled it it was actually just right.  a couple inches.  It was EXTREMELY easy to put together.  Snap the legs into the table and done!!  no tools needed.  I had my screw driver and mallet all ready!!  it was ready to be filled in less than a minute from getting it out of the box.  I love it has a cover to so there isn't as much evaporation and no creepy crawlies are floating in it by morning.  I have only left the water in a few days before changing it so it doesn't get nasty.  My only complaint is water got down into the legs.  There are little holes on the top of the legs just below the table itself.  Water would get in there even if we didn't use it as a water table.  When cleaning it or if it rained water would still fill these little holes.  We just took a drill to the bottom of the legs for drain holes and the water came out!  We have had it for a couple months now and my son loves it.

We've played it with 2 players and 4 players and have had fun with both.  It is a beautifully constructed game board with really high quality game cards and pieces.  The game feels faster-paced than other strategy games (compare Settlers) because each player only does one action per turn (so there is less lag).  It is fun and engaging.

product_title: Banpresto One Piece Princess Shirahoshi Scultures 8.5" Figure
review_body:
This is an extremely affordable figure for what you're getting. The sculpt and painting are detailed and precise -- the figure I received had no real flaws to speak of. She stands about 6" from the base to the highest tip of her hair. One thing that isn't too clear from most pictures is that she does have a slanted fetal pose rather than an upright one. This allows her to be displayed very well from her left side (or straight-on), but her right side isn't really an option because of the angle -- a potentially important consideration for your display configuration.

There is some minor assembly required; she comes in 4 pieces: Head/hair, body, coral/rock, and the actual black base itself. Since the coral's peg cannot be fully inserted except in the proper position, there's no way to assemble her incorrectly.

Overall, I'd say you couldn't possibly ask for a better figure at this price point, especially considering how expensive other Princess Shirahoshi figures are. Collectors rejoice!

product_title: Play-Doh 10-Pack of Colors (Amazon Exclusive)
review_headline: Playdoh is Fun, But You're Getting Tiny Containers for the Price
review_body:
I bought these for my 3 year old daughter and I read the item description carefully prior to purchasing, so I knew I wasn't getting the full sized containers, but I thought I was getting the next size down. Well, I was disappointed by how TINY they are. They are basically the size of the party favor Playdoh containers, which to be honest, you can't make much with. The item photo is quite deceiving because it makes the containers look larger than they really are. I could've paid about 99 cents per container at Walmart for the FULL size ones and only spent an extra $3 more than what I paid for these miniscule containers.

I do like the assortment of colors you get: green, blue, pink, purple, red, black, brown, yellow, orange, and white. Though the Playdoh provides hours of fun for the kids, just know that you are getting small containers for this price.

review_headline: the actual use of the loaded arrows was quite fun for the entire family
review_body: Assembly on the bow was a bit difficult to figure out, so I wish the directions were a bit clearer. Once you bypass the assembly, the actual use of the loaded arrows was quite fun for the entire family, regardless of age. The trigger worked wonderfully in dropping the arrows down to the barrel and all that's needed is to cock and shoot the arrow. The only part I didn't quite like was the quality of the string on the bow and the "feathers" on the arrows were too small. The small "feathers" on the bow often caused the arrow to flip 360 degrees sometimes and the back of the arrow would hit the target at times.

product_title: California Costumes Soul Taker Child Costume
review_body: I bought this costume for my 8 year old son and he really liked it. It's made very well and is sturdy enough to where it made it through the gentle wash cycle without any mishaps. This costume is perfect for kids who want to be scary enough without over doing it. My son had no problems with being able to see out the mask during the day or at night. The costume does run a little long and only the very bottom of the costume would sometimes drag on the ground. But even after a whole night of walking around, the costume remained in tact and the bottom hem had no rips or tears.

product_title: Pokemon Plush Toy - Umbreon (Size L) Around 32cm or 12 + Pokemon Sticker by Doll
review_headline: Lovely Lunar Feline -- The BEST Umbreon Plush!
review_body:
Although this is not an “official” Pokémon product, this Umbreon plush is no doubt the biggest, cutest, softest, and BEST Umbreon available! It “purr-fectly” depicts this beautiful lunar black cat, just as he looks in the Pokémon games, with vivid colours, and spot-on accurate details.

You will not find a single identifying tag on this plush (no hang tag or tush tag), as it is a custom pattern based directly on the awesome TakaraTomy small Umbreon ([[ASIN:B00A84G21E Takaratomy Pokemon N-47 Umbreon/Blacky Best Wishes 8" Plush Doll]]) plush pattern (I have attached photos to compare the two) – only expanded to two times the size! It is a perfect replica of the real Umbreon, accurately designed, and not one detail is missing.

This Umbreon is very lifelike, and large – approximately 13 inches tall! He sits up on his own, excellently balanced, without any need for extra support, so you can easily display him on a bed, shelf, desk, or anywhere you would like.

The materials used to make this plush are high-quality. Like other reviewers mentioned, this Umbreon special in that the material used to make his fur is actually jet-black instead of the more grayish-black-looking shades used on some of the other Umbreon plushies by TakaraTomy and Banpresto. The black "fur" is also very soft and velvety to the touch. The circular golden markings on his forehead and legs are precisely embroidered with shiny bright yellow thread, and his catlike red eyes with slit pupils (also masterfully embroidered onto the face), are piercing and intense, true to the real Umbreon. He has a short feline muzzle with a tiny triangular black nose, and a cute little grin (although these details are somewhat difficult to see at first, as they blend in with his jet-black fur). All over, his figure is perfect and accurate! He is stuffed to purr-fection, and although he is very lithe in shape, he is super-soft, squishy, and very cuddly. His rabbit-like ears are stuffed thickly, so they stand upright do not flop, and they have beautiful golden yellow ring patterns around them. The tail is the same, constructed and well-stuffed, just like the ears. His feline paws and feet are very beautifully detailed, with digits sewn in. His lovely detailed front paws are sewn together by thick threads, and I would not advise separating them, as it might result in damaging the plush.

Being an Eeveelution fanatic and cat lover, I adore Umbreon (as well has his Psychic-type sister, Espeon), and could not be more delighted with this incredible plush. He is one of my top favourites, and is always there for me to cuddle. He is perfect to snuggle with; hugging a soft plushie comforts me and helps me sleep, and this Umbreon has become one of my main cuddle buddies. I call him "Phantom". :)

I ordered this beautiful extra-large Umbreon plush from a very kind and honest seller on eBay. These extra-large Eeveelution plushies are made in and sold from China, so it will take some time to ship, but it is worth the wait. Again, this is not an official Nintendo plush, but in my personal opinion it is actually better and more fairly priced than any official Umbreon plush currently available. I have both the small TakaraTomy Umbreon and the Banpresto “I Love Eevee” large Umbreon, but this Umbreon is my favourite because it is so large and soft. It is a truly awesome size, durable, well-made, and so cute! Highly recommended to children and collectors -- and cat lovers, of course! ♥ike ears are stuffed thickly, so they stand upright do not flop, and they have beautiful golden yellow ring patterns around them. His lovely detailed front paws are sewn together by thick threads, and I would not advise separating them, as it might result in damaging the plush.

product_title: Devil Horns, Tail, and Bow Tie Set
review_body:
I love Halloween, yet whenever I have an occasion where I need to wear a costume, I feel like I can never find anything or have a hard time coming up with something. This set is great because it is easily made into a quick and fun costume. It is especially fun for me because I am generally viewed as the "good girl" in my circles, so dressing the opposite is a blast. You can really do it up wearing all red or you can make it pretty simple. You can also dress conservatively or you can really make it sexy if that is the look you are going for. I like that such simple pieces can lead to such a versatile costume. The sequins add a fun blingy touch to the costume without being overboard and they stay put (which is often an issue with sequins).
Is this the best devil costume out there? No, but then again, you aren't paying an arm and a leg for it like many of the other kits out there, yet it is still a nice quality. The only reason that I gave it four stars instead of five is that the horns are just a little bit floppy. I'm not sure if every costume is that way or if something happened to mine during shipping, but it doesn't take away from the costume. It still looks like devil horns.
Overall, a fun costume set that I'm glad to have on hand.
I received this product at a discounted price in exchange for my honest and unbiased opinion and review.

product_title: R Prism Racing Tire, Pink Compound (2): RU, ST VXL

They are the only tire I have found which does not come unglued or explode once 60mph is exceeded. The manufacturing of this tire and the treated foam material are what permits highspeed stability. The only drawback is they wear down and can chunk-up on rough streets and they are not good off-road or in wet conditions. That said, best dry street tire that can handle high speeds.

review_headline: but the first Easy Clean-type mat
review_body: This is the third Wildkin nap mat I have purchased for my children to use in preschool, but the first Easy Clean-type mat. While I wholeheartedly recommend the Wildkin brand, I can't recommend the Easy Clean Nap Mats. They are made of a slick fabric that makes noise when you touch it. My child loved lying down in the nap mat, but wouldn't sleep in it because he was too busy rubbing the fabric and wiggling in it, enjoying the noise it made and the way the mat slid across the carpet when he would move. I am sending this nap mat back. For the record, though, I would absolutely buy one of the regular Wildkin nap mats again. They have lasted each of my two older children throughout their preschool years, even with weekly (or more often) washings.

product_title: WowWee Robotic Enhanced Vehicles (R.E.V)
review_body:
This is definitely the next generation of toys. And it's definitely for "children" 8++. I say "children" because adults will love the cars just as much as 8 year olds.

First off, you need a smartphone or other smart device to serve as the remote. For full compatibility list, visit www.wowweezone.com. But more recent iPhones and Android devices are included in the list.

With the smartphone or device, you can choose the game that you want the cars to play and choose how and when they shoot each other and which weapons they use. You'll also need 8 AA batteries. I suggest that you use rechargeable batteries. I tend to recharge the car batteries when I recharge my cell phone, and I haven't run into low batteries at inopportune times by following that routine.

You end up controlling one of the cars and the other car automatically responds to the car you're controlling. It's like a live video game. So you don't need to control the second car yourself. I read that GPS tracking technology allows the second car to follow the first. Not only does the second car follow the first, but it shoots at it and tries to "destroy" it. So you need to make sure that your car wins the game.

You can play the game on any floor surface. The cars, though, move fastest on smoother surfaces. Luckily, they didn't scratch my floors.

Finally, you can buy accessories--if you want. You can buy ramps. You can also buy additional cars. I read that you can have up to 50 cars playing the game at once. I'm not exactly sure how that works, though.

product_title: Crayola Crayon Carver
review_body:
People who like to personalize their crayons are likely to enjoy this crayon carver. It does work and my children customized a number of crayons with just a little of my help, mostly removing stuck tiles.

The crayons have to be the correct length, which is new or almost new. They have a Crayola Crayon Maker but, unfortunately, it produces crayons that are too short to be used in this carver. It would be better if this could carve different length crayons.

From my limited usage, I would give it four stars. My daughter rated it three and a half stars.

Her review:
This is really fun. It doesn’t require you to handle any sharp objects to cut shapes into the crayon and the result is nice. However, some of the designs are unclear and certain tiles got stuck in the slots; I could not pull them out. The wrapper ripper works okay, but it causes an unsightly line to be carved into the crayon’s side.
